on started...but why take the risk? Remember to collect!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','A Cut Above the Rest','','publish','open','open','','a-cut-above-the-rest','','','2019-12-22 16:55:45','2019-12-22 16:55:45','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1671',0,'post','',0),(1673,8,'2019-12-19 20:14:16','2019-12-19 20:14:16','','Knife Giving Feature','','inherit','open','closed','','knife-giving-feature','','','2019-12-19 20:14:16','2019-12-19 20:14:16','',1671,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Knife-Giving-Feature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1674,8,'2019-12-19 20:14:29','2019-12-19 20:14:29','','Knife Giving Thumbnail','','inherit','open','closed','','knife-giving-thumbnail','','','2019-12-19 20:14:29','2019-12-19 20:14:29','',1671,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Knife-Giving-Thumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1675,8,'2020-01-03 22:32:09','2020-01-03 22:32:09','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Good leather pieces are built not only to last a lifetime but to look the better for it.&nbsp;<br><br>Constructed from 100% vegetable-tanned skirting leather, we’re less concerned with how to keep <a href=\"https://www.bestmadeco.com/bags/leather\">our bags and accessories</a> looking perfectly new than we are with keeping them in good condition — after all, a little wear and tear just adds character.&nbsp;<br><br>Whether it’s a wallet, a briefcase, or belt, there are a few basic steps that will help you keep your leather in tip-top shape.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>LEATHER CARE TIPS</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Perhaps obvious, but — <strong>keep things clean</strong>. A quick wipe with a soft damp cloth is good for weekly upkeep. Use specially formulated leather cleaners for more intensive care.<br><br></li><li><strong>Store your leather the right way</strong>. Which is to say, away from lots of sun, humidity, heat, and so on. Leather <em>can</em> degrade with too much moisture, so just make sure to air things out now and then. <br><br></li><li>It’s bound to get wet at some point. When it does, <strong>gently blot</strong> the affected spots as soon as you’re able — do <em>not</em> rub or use something like a blowdryer to speed things up.<br><br></li><li>Conversely, if your leather becomes too dry, you can <strong>use a <a href=\"https://bestmadeco.com/products/leather-care-liniment-no-1\">leather liniment</a></strong> (more on that below) to re-condition it.&nbsp;</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When it comes to re-conditioning, our product of choice is the <a href=\"https://bestmadeco.com/products/leather-care-liniment-no-1\">Leather Care Liniment No. 1 from Chamberlain’s Leather Milk</a> —&nbsp;the Best Made designers love this product because it’s so exceptionally gentle.&nbsp;<br><br>Environmentally friendly and made from cosmetic-grade ingredients, it’s easy and safe to use on nearly any type of leather: shoes, boots, bags, luggage, and more or all fair game. It’s especially ideal for naturally-tanned or unfinished leathers — but don’t use it on “soft” leathers like suede, nubuck, napped, or genuine leather.&nbsp;<br><br>Conditioners enrich the natural color of the leather and give it a soft, supple texture — they also actively strengthen the fibers, which means it will live longer, too.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>HOW TO RE-CONDITION YOUR LEATHER</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Always check any care recommendations included by the manufacturer before doing anything else. Unless they indicate otherwise, start by testing a small amount of the liniment in a discreet spot, allowing it to dry in a cool area, away from sun and heat. If it doesn’t discolor, you’re good to go.&nbsp;<br><br></li><li>Clean your leather with a damp, soft cloth if it’s dirty, and then wait for it to dry.&nbsp;<br><br></li><li>Shake the liniment to combine, and then massage it an even, thin layer across the entire surface of the leather — the more even, the less likely you are to end up with a spotty finish. You can add more coats, but beware going too thick; it can leave a sticky residue.<br><br></li><li>Allow the leather to dry naturally, and when it has absorbed all the conditioner it can, buff off any remaining residue and let it set. For best results, allow it to sit somewhere dry and clean overnight.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can condition your leather goods 2-4 times a year or as often as they need it; really whenever it starts to feel rough or dry. Conditioning may darken your leather a bit, but don’t worry — it should lighten back up after a few days. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','How-To: Leather Care','','publish','open','open','','how-to-leather-care','','','2020-01-17 19:40:46','2020-01-17 19:40:46','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1675',0,'post','',0),(1676,8,'2019-12-19 20:36:05','2019-12-19 20:36:05','','Leather Care Feature','','inherit','open','closed','','leather-care-feature','','','2019-12-19 20:36:05','2019-12-19 20:36:05','',1675,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Leather-Care-Feature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1677,8,'2019-12-19 20:36:15','2019-12-19 20:36:15','','Leather Care Thumbnail','','inherit','open','closed','','leather-care-thumbnail','','','2019-12-19 20:36:15','2019-12-19 20:36:15','',1675,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Leather-Care-Thumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1636,8,'2019-12-09 19:38:53','2019-12-09 19:38:53','','10 Wilderness Travel Tips Feature','','inherit','open','closed','','10-wilderness-travel-tips-feature','','','2019-12-09 19:38:53','2019-12-09 19:38:53','',1633,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/10-Wilderness-Travel-Tips-Feature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1637,8,'2019-12-09 19:39:43','2019-12-09 19:39:43','','10 Wilderness Travel Tips Thumbnail','','inherit','open','closed','','10-wilderness-travel-tips-thumbnail','','','2019-12-09 19:39:43','2019-12-09 19:39:43','',1633,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/10-Wilderness-Travel-Tips-Thumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1692