22:01:16','','Slider 732 - image','','publish','closed','closed','','slider-732-image-4','','','2019-11-07 17:59:20','2019-11-07 17:59:20','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=ml-slide&#038;p=736',3,'ml-slide','',0),(737,8,'2019-11-05 22:01:25','2019-11-05 22:01:25','','Slider 732 - image','','publish','closed','closed','','slider-732-image-5','','','2019-11-07 17:59:20','2019-11-07 17:59:20','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=ml-slide&#038;p=737',4,'ml-slide','',0),(738,8,'2019-11-05 22:01:36','2019-11-05 22:01:36','','Slider 732 - image','','publish','closed','closed','','slider-732-image-6','','','2019-11-07 17:59:20','2019-11-07 17:59:20','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=ml-slide&#038;p=738',5,'ml-slide','',0),(860,8,'2019-02-13 16:10:19','2019-02-13 16:10:19','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":40} -->\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6} -->\n<h6><em>In pursuit of leading an extraordinary life, Best Made provides team members the opportunity to apply for an Adventure Grant — a stipend and a week of paid leave to undertake the adventure of their dreams. </em></h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>John MacLean, our Client Services Manager and latest Grant recipient, knew exactly what to do with his time off: visit the Great North Woods, where he spent summers in awe of the Algonquin canoe makers of the nearby Kitigan-Zibi Anishinaabe community in Quebec.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator {\"className\":\"is-style-dots\"} -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator is-style-dots\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1247,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":512,\"height\":463} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/John-MaClean-1024x925.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1247\" width=\"512\" height=\"463\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I was struck by the birch canoe the moment I laid eyes on one: a vessel built completely by hand and completely from the earth; a vessel without which North America would be vastly different. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To me, no adventure so embodied the Best Made culture and mission like putting my own hands to hard work and utilizing our own gear and apparel to learn and build with a community of creators, perhaps more in-sync with their natural world than any I’ve ever known. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pinock Smith is a native of the Kitigan Zibi Anishinabeg in Quebec. He has specialized in making traditional Algonquin crafts for decades, with a particular focus on the birchbark canoe, as well as traditional paddles, cradleboards, toboggans, and drums. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Pinock doesn’t like to actually canoe, but making them is in his blood. He was mesmerized by his uncle’s canoe-craft and learned the skill from him, continuing a family tradition across countless generations. </p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He is regarded as an elder and mentor to many in his community, both for his skill with and knowledge of traditional Algonquin crafts and his fluency in the Algonquin language —&nbsp;as well as his willingness to teach others the same.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nearly five decades later, Pinock continues to build traditional Anishinaabe birch canoes — and I was honored to learn from him.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator {\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator is-style-default\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">A Complete (<em>But Inexhaustive</em>) Guide to Building a Canoe</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":40} -->\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaId\":1237,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Canoe-Step1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1237\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\">Collect your materials. I spent three days in the bush collecting spruce roots and gum, cedar, birch, and ash.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaPosition\":\"right\",\"mediaId\":1238,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide has-media-on-the-right\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Canoe-Step2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1238\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\">Prepare the materials: strip and split all roots, eighth the cedar and square it off, and remove the birch bark.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaId\":1239,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Canoe-Step3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1239\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Determine the size and shape of your inwales, and then shave them — this will make the inside form of the canoe. Construct the outwhales and gunwales.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaPosition\":\"right\",\"mediaId\":1240,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide has-media-on-the-right\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Canoe-Step4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1240\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\">Fold the bark to your form, making cuts as needed to properly shape the canoe.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaId\":1241,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Canoe-Step5.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1241\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\">Use the spruce root to sew the birch bark between the inwales and outwales, taking care to raise the bow and stern.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaPosition\":\"right\",\"mediaId\":1242,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide has-media-on-the-right\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Canoe-Step6.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1242\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\">Form the cedar ribs and let them dry inside the canoe to take shape.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaId\":1243,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Canoe-Step7.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1243\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\">Split the cedar sheeting and insert it before inserting the dried, formed ribbings.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaPosition\":\"right\",\"mediaId\":1244,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide has-media-on-the-right\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Canoe-Step8.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1244\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\">Peg gunwales to each side of the canoe, drilling and inserting the wooden pegs one-by-one, starting in the middle.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaId\":1245,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Canoe-Step9.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1245\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\">Filter the spruce gum, add bear fat, and apply to the cut creases around the canoe, the bow, and stern.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">Anchors away!</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer -->\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Building a Canoe','','publish','open','open','','building-a-canoe','','','2019-11-14 22:19:59','2019-11-14 22:19:59','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=860',0,'post','',0),(1709,8,'2020-01-06 15:46:42','2020-01-06 15:46:42','','Leather Belt','','inherit','open','closed','','leather-belt','','','2020-01-06 15:46:42','2020-01-06 15:46:42','',1708,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Leather-Belt.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1710,8,'2020-01-10 19:07:39','2020-01-10 19:07:39','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Every metal is unique — copper develops a green patina, brass is weak to salt, stainless steel is protected by chromium — but in the end, they all rust.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The truth of the matter is that when metal of any sort comes into contact with air and moisture, it immediately starts to oxidize. It’s not even as simple as keeping something dry; anything organic contains moisture, so sweat, food, tobacco, even a particularly humid day...all of it can cause metal to tarnish.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To ensure your pieces last for decades, first, you need to know how to prevent tarnish from developing in the first place — and then, what to do when rust inevitably appears.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":40} -->\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>METAL CARE TIPS</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li><strong>Handle with care.</strong> When it comes to metal, even the salts and oils in our hands can cause damage; if something is precious, handle it with clean hands or wear gloves.&nbsp;<br><br></li><li>Excessive light, heat, and moisture all trigger corrosion. <strong>Store metal in a dry, cool place,</strong> and away from wooden items or furniture, which can release harmful acidic vapors.<br><br></li><li><strong>Water is the enemy</strong> — if your metal gets wet, wipe it dry immediately with a clean cloth, and never leave it sitting around on a drying rack.<br><br></li><li>If your item won’t be in use for a month or more, wipe the surface with mineral oil (extra virgin olive oil works too, especially for kitchen items) now and then to prevent corrosion. <strong>Regular maintenance is key.</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":40} -->\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once metal has started to tarnish, it’s important to treat it quickly and thoroughly. The <a href=\"https://bestmadeco.com/products/cape-cod-metal-polishing-cloths\">Cape Cod Metal Polishing Cloths</a> are something of a miracle product, and make metal maintenance a breeze. You can use them on any type of metal, too, and they’re safe and easy to use.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":40} -->\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>HOW TO POLISH YOUR METAL</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1711,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":450,\"height\":300} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Metal-Care-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1711\" width=\"450\" height=\"300\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>First, wipe your item clean with a dry cloth to remove any surface grime.&nbsp;<br><br></li><li>Then, take one of the reusable Cape Cod cloths and vigorously polish the surface of your item for 5-10 minutes, putting in a little extra elbow grease on the especially tarnished areas.&nbsp;<br><br></li><li>Because the cloths break down the residue on the metal, they (and your hands!) will naturally darken as you polish. When you’re done, simply wipe off the now-liquid residue.<br><br></li><li>To finish, buff the item clean with a new dry cloth.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":40} -->\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you’re done, your piece should have its original, beautiful shine back — and the cloths impart an anti-tarnish finish, too. To make sure they retain their polishing power as possible, make sure to store them in an airtight container.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If your piece already has significant rust on it, the polish cloths may not be enough. In that case, you can try the following:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Soak your item in plain white vinegar for 24-48 hours.&nbsp;</li><li>Use a clean cloth to rub off the remaining residue.</li><li>Use a polishing stone on stubborn spots, taking care to work in the direction of any established grind to avoid marks.</li><li>Wipe clean to finish.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the proper care, your blades, watches, lighters, and more will all stay in top condition for years to come.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','How-To: Metal Care','','publish','open','open','','how-to-metal-care','','','2020-01-17 19:40:41','2020-01-17 19:40:41','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1710',0,'post','',0),(471,8,'2019-10-30 22:12:06','2019-10-30 22:12:06','<iframe title=\"Johnny Cash - Cremation of Sam McGee\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/yJNZwuamwj0?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>','','','publish','closed','closed','','d242ded6cf037b286a9313cdfae70a9c','','','2019-10-30 22:12:06','2019-10-30 22:12:06','',0,'https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/uncategorized/d242ded6cf037b286a9313cdfae70a9c/',0,'oembed_cache','',0),(1704,8,'2020-01-06 15:45:37','2020-01-06 15:45:37','','The Small Horizontal Gfeller Document Case','','publish','closed','closed','','the-small-horizontal-gfeller-document-case','','','2020-01-06 15:45:37','2020-01-06 15:45:37','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=1704',0,'product','',0),(1705,8,'2020-01-06 15:45:29','2020-01-06 15:45:29','','Leather Small Horizontal Case','','inherit','open','closed','','leather-small-horizontal-case','','','2020-01-06 15:45:29','2020-01-06 15:45:29','',1704,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Leather-Small-Horizontal-Case.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1706,8,'2020-01-06 15:46:08','2020-01-06 15:46:08','','The Large Horizontal Gfeller Document Case','','publish','closed','closed','','the-large-horizontal-gfeller-document-case','','','2020-01-06 15:46:08','2020-01-06 15:46:08','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=1706',0,'product','',0),(1707,8,'2020-01-06 15:46:00','2020-01-06 15:46:00','','Leather Large Horizontal Case','','inherit','open','closed','','leather-large-horizontal-case','','','2020-01-06 15:46:00','2020-01-06 15:46:00','',1706,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Leather-Large-Horizontal-Case.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1708,8,'2020-01-06 15:46:47','2020-01-06 15:46:47','','The Best Made Standard Belt','','publish','closed','closed','','the-best-made-standard-belt','','','2020-01-06 15:46:47','2020-01-06 15:46:47','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=1708',0,'product','',0),(346,8,'2019-08-11 16:30:38','2019-08-11 16:30:38','<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">When it comes to choosing the best camping knife, first you need to decide: folding or fixed? A fixed blade is significantly more capable, at the cost of additional weight and less convenient carry. A folding knife is more packable and adaptable, but the design is inherently less secure (only two slipjoints made it on our list).&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">How you’ll be using it is key. Will you be carving tent stakes, batoning firewood, or clearing brush? A more heavy-duty, full-tang knife is worth packing. If the most action your knife will see is nipping some paracord to length, dressing a trout, or slicing salami, a smaller, precision-focused knife is appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">There’s a lot of information ahead; we’ve summarized the specs in a table at the end. The blades in this list are arranged from most capable to most specialized, giving an idea of what we account for when picking the right knife to take camping. There is no single all-around “best camping knife” — but this will help you pick the right knife for the job.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":889,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Olivewood.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-889\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>1. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.bestmadeco.com/products/solingen-field-knife-olivewood\" target=\"_blank\">Solingen Field Knife Olivewood</a> / $148.00 </strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">It should come as no surprise that we’re typically not far from an axe or hatchet — but when it comes to needing a knife that provides a decent chop, we bring along Solingen Field Knife. Beautifully made from stainless 440C steel and olivewood scales, it’s both elegant and resilient. Any knife that will see vigorous use (whether that includes gathering firewood or dressing big game) needs an unfailing grip, which the Field Knife achieves with its substantial integrated finger guard. With a full tang construction, exceptional hardness at 57 HRC, and a handsome leather sheath, the Solingen Field Knife is a formidable choice if you only have room for one knife in your rig.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"is-style-stripes medium-table\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter is-style-stripes medium-table\"><tbody><tr><td><strong>Blade Length</strong></td><td>4”</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Overall Length</strong></td><td>8.5”</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Steel&nbsp;</strong></td><td>440C</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Best For</strong></td><td>All-Purpose</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":378,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":394,\"height\":305} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Screen-Shot-2019-09-26-at-12.46.56-PM-2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-378\" width=\"394\" height=\"305\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>2. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"http://ontarioknife.com/fixed-blades/black-bird/black-bird-sk-5.html\" target=\"_blank\">OKC Black Bird</a> / $173.95 </strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">The OKC Black Bird is truly a “final word” kind of knife, one of our top choices for true dependability. With full-tang 154 CM high carbon, stainless steel and G-10 scales, it takes top marks in toughness, sharpness, and durability. The spear-point profile consistently proves its versatility, while the handle shape offers a stable grip without limiting options for hand positions. With a design influenced by bushcraft blades and military survival knives, the Black Bird has a spartan appeal and an optional MOLLE sheath. A great knife to throw on the belt once the packs are dropped, we’ve never had to wonder if it would be able to handle the job.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"large-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter large-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td>Blade Length</td><td>5”</td></tr><tr><td>Overall Length</td><td>10”</td></tr><tr><td>Steel&nbsp;</td><td>154 CM</td></tr><tr><td>Best For</td><td>Bushcraft/ Survival</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":890,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Case-Stacked.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-890\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">3. <a href=\"https://www.bestmadeco.com/products/case-stacked-leather-hunting-knife?taxon_id=1569\">The Case Stacked Leather Hunting Knife</a> / $98</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">The Case Hunter Knife is about as classic as it gets for an American camping knife and provides a balance between size and cutting dexterity. With a handsome leather sheath, contoured stacked leather handle, and high-polish finish, it’s a true heritage piece that’s ready to work. The Tru-Sharp stainless steel is highly rust-resistant, and the concave grind makes for a knife that is both tough yet incredibly sharp. The clip-point blade provides a precise tip for careful work, while the overall length offers a consistent cut for those who plan to serve up a full venison sirloin in the field. The concave grind does mean this knife is better suited for precise slicing than hard chopping.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"medium-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter medium-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td>Blade Length</td><td>5”</td></tr><tr><td>Overall Length</td><td>9”</td></tr><tr><td>Steel&nbsp;</td><td>Tru-Sharp Stainless</td></tr><tr><td>Best For</td><td>Camp Cooking</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":380,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":506,\"height\":315} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Screen-Shot-2019-09-26-at-12.50.50-PM-2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380\" width=\"506\" height=\"315\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>4. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.spyderco.com/catalog/details/C81G2/Para-Military-2-G-10-Black/472\" target=\"_blank\">Spyderco Para Military</a> / $216.00 </strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">The Spyderco folding knife has become a modern classic, and the Para Military is our go-to when we want to carry a folder with fixed-blade performance. With an S30V blade - one of the most advanced high-alloy stainless blades on the market - and G-10 scales, it’s built to endure heavy use in absolutely any environment. The recognizable Spyderco shape provides an ergonomic handle for various grips and is replete with jimping for extra stability while bearing down through a tough slice. The Para Military has a well-engineered locking mechanism that gives us the confidence to treat it like a fixed blade, and four options for clip position make it easy to adapt to any carry style. An excellent survival blade to throw into the glove box as a “Plan B” knife when another blade failed or was forgotten.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"large-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter large-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td>Blade Length</td><td>3.4”</td></tr><tr><td>Overall Length</td><td>8.3”</td></tr><tr><td>Steel&nbsp;</td><td>CPM S30V</td></tr><tr><td>Best For</td><td>Backup All-Purpose</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":891,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/FoldingHunting.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-891\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>5. </strong><a href=\"https://www.bestmadeco.com/products/laguiole-folding-hunting-knife?taxon_id=1569\">The Laguiole Folding Hunting Knife</a><strong> / $398</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">The Laguiole Folding Hunter is a true blade lover’s camp knife. Crafted by some of the world’s finest cutlers in France, it features fine handiwork, elegant lines, and robust utility. While Laguiole is best known for their penknives, the Folding Hunter steps up to camp work with a high-carbon stainless blade and hefty size. The wide blade and slender juniper handle make it comfortable enough for both a long slice and for choking up on the blade to get detailed. The perfect knife to accompany the camper whose legendary fireside stories are the highlight of the night, the Folding Hunter is a blade with both capability and charisma.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"small-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter small-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td>Blade Length</td><td>4.5”</td></tr><tr><td>Overall Length</td><td>9.7”</td></tr><tr><td>Steel&nbsp;</td><td>14C28N</td></tr><tr><td>Best For</td><td>Hefty Pack Knife</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":892,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Makiri.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-892\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>6. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.bestmadeco.com/products/makiri-fishermans-knife?taxon_id=1569\" target=\"_blank\">Makiri Fisherman\'s Knife</a> / $118</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">The Makiri Fishing Knife is a lightweight, packable fixed blade that provides a uniquely Japanese experience. The hand-hammered, laminate high-carbon steel blade is ground with a single bevel for cutting ability that far surpasses the typical double-bevel edge. The Makiri is truly a working-class blade, built to maintain its incredible sharpness through a day’s worth of rigorous camping tasks, from slicing greenwood to chopping vegetables. Relatively lightweight, the magnolia handle and <em>saya</em> (seamless wooden sheath) allow for convenient, safe storage in a backpack. For those who are daunted by the thought of taking a high-carbon blade into the wilderness — don’t be. While high-carbon steel is prone to rust at first, it will quickly develop a patina that reduces its need for maintenance drastically, and the steel’s ability to take and keep an edge is peerless. Regardless of a knife’s steel composition, it’s polite to wipe down any blade before returning it to the sheath.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"large-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter large-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td>Blade Length</td><td>5.3”</td></tr><tr><td>Overall Length</td><td>10.6”</td></tr><tr><td>Steel&nbsp;</td><td>High-carbon laminate</td></tr><tr><td>Best For</td><td>Packable All-Purpose</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":894,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Juniper.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-894\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>7. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"THE PROVINCIAL JUNIPER KNIFE (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.bestmadeco.com/products/provincial-juniper-knife\" target=\"_blank\">The Provincial Juniper Knife</a> / $298 </strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">The Provincial Juniper Knife is for the backcountry angler. An elegant piece of hardware to match the sophistication of fly fishing tackle, it’s a stunning example of French cutlery that performs flawlessly. The blade has a surgical tip for careful work when splicing leader to tippet, and ample length for efficiently gutting the day’s catch. The blade is crafted from Sandvik 19C27, stainless high-carbon steel with high hardness preferred by chefs for its performance in demanding environments. Robust yet lightweight, the Juniper Knife disappears into a pocket or chest pouch, and a liner lock provides secure use while slicing through summer sausage. An elegant blade built for precision and sharpness, it’s not intended for significant leverage or rough work.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"medium-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter medium-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td>Blade Length</td><td>3.5”</td></tr><tr><td>Overall Length</td><td>7.8”</td></tr><tr><td>Steel&nbsp;</td><td>19C27</td></tr><tr><td>Best For</td><td>Precision Slicing</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":895,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/American-Trapper.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-895\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>8. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.bestmadeco.com/products/american-trapper-knife\" target=\"_blank\">The American Trapper Knife</a> / $148 </strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">The Case American Trapper is a collection-worthy piece that begs to be used. The perfect blade for a camper who prefers using a knife for meal prep, light tasks, and whittling, it’s a handsome example of American craftsmanship that every young scout would be glad to inherit. The polished finish adds to the durability of the Tru-Sharp surgical stainless steel and bone handle, while the thumb stud and liner lock make for predictable one-handed use. A knife pattern that has been around for centuries, the America Trapper Knife is an unassuming camp favorite that works wonders. Best carried as a sharp companion knife while a larger blade does the grunt work.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"medium-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter medium-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td>Blade Length</td><td>3”</td></tr><tr><td>Overall Length</td><td>7.5”</td></tr><tr><td>Steel&nbsp;</td><td>Tru-Sharp</td></tr><tr><td>Best For</td><td>Pocket Whittler</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":896,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Otter-Green.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-896\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>9. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"OTTER GREEN FOLDING KNIFE (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.bestmadeco.com/products/otter-green-folding-knife\" target=\"_blank\">The Otter Green Folding Knife</a> / $88 </strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">The scalpel-like appearance of the Otter Green Folding Knife is a product of its medical origin, yet we’ve found endless camp utility for this surgical blade. With a lengthy handle, extended ricasso with a thumb indent, and a precision blade, it excels as a bird and trout knife for upland hunters and alpine anglers. The dyed-bone scales are not only durable, but a handsome match to the plumage of a pheasant or mallard. The handle-to-blade ratio provides the necessary control for breasting a quail or fireside whittling, while the stainless steel blade holds up well against blood and moisture. While we would suggest that only those with professional training attempt any debriding or suturing, this German-made knife is certainly up to the task.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"large-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter large-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td>Blade Length</td><td>2.5”</td></tr><tr><td>Overall Length</td><td>6.85”</td></tr><tr><td>Steel&nbsp;</td><td>Stainless</td></tr><tr><td>Best For</td><td>Bird and Trout</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":388,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/imlay-orange.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-388\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>10. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.eseeknives.com/product/imlay-rescue\" target=\"_blank\">ESEE Imlay Rescue</a> / $129.16 </strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">We acknowledge that not all campsites are reached by land, so we\'ve included our favorite water-ready knife. The ESEE Imlay Rescue was designed with a blunt tip for use around inflatable watercraft, ropes under tension, or trapped swimmers. The 440C stainless steel blade has exceptional rust resistance, and the sheath features an additional retention strap for extremely secure carry over rough waters. The Imlay was modified from ESEE\'s legendary Izula knife, and transitions effortlessly between PFD carry and shoreside work. The partially serrated edge speaks to its intended use around cordage, while the plain-edge tip provides versatility for camping tasks. Accompanied by a sheath clip and paracord (for an optional handle wrap), it offers every sailor, rafter, or kayaker a personal method of attachment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"small-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter small-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td>Blade Length</td><td>2.25”</td></tr><tr><td>Overall Length</td><td>5.9”</td></tr><tr><td>Steel&nbsp;</td><td>440C</td></tr><tr><td>Best For</td><td>Watercraft</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":897,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Hobo.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-897\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>11. <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.bestmadeco.com/products/branded-hobo-knife?taxon_id=1569\" target=\"_blank\">The Hobo Knife</a> / $48&nbsp;</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">Although the Hobo Knife is only 1/3 knife, it has earned a permanent place in our kitchen kit. We’ve found that eating utensils work best when they don’t try to accomplish too much at once (looking at you, sporks), and the Hobo Knife has the crucial ability to detach fork from knife from spoon. For those who prefer not to skimp on the camp spread, having three utensils to cook with is particularly useful, especially when all three pack down into a convenient nylon sheath. As this is a knife list, we haven’t overlooked the central folding knife — a dedicated eating utensil, it doesn’t see the same kind of rough action as a belt knife, so its capably sharp edge lasts quite a while, and the full stainless-steel construction requires little maintenance. When our primary camping knife has gotten a bit dull, we’ve turned to the Hobo Knife for cleaning brook trout.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"medium-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter medium-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td>Blade Length</td><td>3”</td></tr><tr><td>Overall Length</td><td>6.625”</td></tr><tr><td>Steel&nbsp;</td><td>420J2</td></tr><tr><td>Best For</td><td>Camp Cooking</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\" class=\"has-normal-font-size\">A tool so fundamental it can’t be improved upon — only adapted and refined — the camp knife takes innumerable forms. Whether a trip calls for a full-tang, high-carbon survival knife, or a durable, stainless steel folding blade is entirely up to the needs of the camper; review the specs below and make the decision for yourself. When in doubt, we rely on an old refrain: the more knives, the better.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"large-table is-style-stripes\"} -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table aligncenter large-table is-style-stripes\"><tbody><tr><td><strong>Knife Name</strong></td><td><strong>Overall Length</strong></td><td><strong>Blade Length</strong></td><td><strong>Handle Material</strong></td><td><strong>Steel</strong></td><td><strong>Price</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Solingen Field Knife</td><td>8.5”</td><td>4”</td><td>Olivewood</td><td>440C Stainless</td><td>$148</td></tr><tr><td>OKC Black Bird</td><td>10”</td><td>5”</td><td>G-10</td><td>154 CM</td><td>$174</td></tr><tr><td>Hunter Knife with Stacked Leather</td><td>9”</td><td>5”</td><td>Stacked Leather</td><td>Tru-Sharp Stainless</td><td>$98</td></tr><tr><td>Spyderco Para Military 2</td><td>8.3”</td><td>3.4”</td><td>G-10</td><td>CPM S30V</td><td>$216</td></tr><tr><td>Laguiole Folding Hunter</td><td>9.7”</td><td>4.5”</td><td>Juniper</td><td>14C28N</td><td>$398</td></tr><tr><td>Buck 110/G-10</td><td>8.5”</td><td>3.75”</td><td>G-10</td><td>CPM S30V</td><td>$178</td></tr><tr><td>Makiri Fishing Knife</td><td>10.6”</td><td>5.3”</td><td>Magnolia</td><td>High-carbon laminate</td><td>$118</td></tr><tr><td>Blaze Orange Sodbuster</td><td>3.6”</td><td>2.8”</td><td>Synthetic</td><td>Tru-Sharp Stainless</td><td>$48</td></tr><tr><td>Provincial Juniper</td><td>7.8”</td><td>3.5”</td><td>Juniper</td><td>19C27</td><td>$298</td></tr><tr><td>Case American Trapper</td><td>7.5”</td><td>3”</td><td>Dyed Bone</td><td>Tru-Sharp Stainless</td><td>$148</td></tr><tr><td>Otter Green Folding Knife</td><td>6.85”</td><td>2.5”</td><td>Dyed Bone</td><td>Stainless&nbsp;</td><td>$88</td></tr><tr><td>ESEE Imlay Rescue</td><td>5.9”</td><td>2.25”</td><td>Full tang</td><td>440C</td><td>$129</td></tr><tr><td>Hobo Knife</td><td>6.625”</td><td>3”</td><td>Stainless</td><td>420J2</td><td>$48</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->','The 11 Best Camping Knives for 2019','','publish','open','open','','the-13-best-camping-knives-for-2019','','','2019-11-14 22:24:04','2019-11-14 22:24:04','',0,'http://bmcoblog.wpengine.com/?p=346',0,'post','',0),(334,2,'2019-08-06 17:51:59','2019-08-06 17:51:59','{\"block-lab\\/product-action\":{\"name\":\"product-action\",\"title\":\"Product Action\",\"icon\":\"view_day\",\"category\":{\"slug\":\"common\",\"title\":\"Common Blocks\",\"icon\":null},\"keywords\":[\"\"],\"fields\":{\"product-image\":{\"name\":\"product-image\",\"label\":\"Product Image\",\"co