age/jpeg',0),(386,8,'2019-09-26 17:05:40','2019-09-26 17:05:40','','1476393160','','inherit','open','closed','','1476393160','','','2019-09-26 17:05:40','2019-09-26 17:05:40','',346,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/1476393160.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(387,8,'2019-09-26 17:06:16','2019-09-26 17:06:16','','bmc_060519_otter_knife_0004_GW_MG','','inherit','open','closed','','bmc_060519_otter_knife_0004_gw_mg','','','2019-09-26 17:06:16','2019-09-26 17:06:16','',346,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/bmc_060519_otter_knife_0004_GW_MG.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(388,8,'2019-09-26 17:07:07','2019-09-26 17:07:07','','imlay-orange','','inherit','open','closed','','imlay-orange','','','2019-09-26 17:07:07','2019-09-26 17:07:07','',346,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/imlay-orange.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(389,8,'2019-09-26 17:07:47','2019-09-26 17:07:47','','1469138217','','inherit','open','closed','','1469138217','','','2019-09-26 17:07:47','2019-09-26 17:07:47','',346,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/1469138217.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(392,8,'2019-09-27 20:34:34','2019-09-27 20:34:34','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In Japan, a dedication to craft elevates the simple to the sublime. Each choice is considered. Objects balance beauty and utility. Tradition informs work, without restricting it. Quality is key. These qualities resonate deeply, and are why we went to Japan. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The stories presented here — from the outdoorsmen to the furniture maker and more — were an opportunity to test our products the best way we know how: by giving them to experts to use in the field.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">The Outdoorsmen</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Satoshi Yamane, who owns and runs the Tokyo outdoor supply store, Root, has long been a friend to Best Made. We met up with him and his friends, Ino Zhèng Zāi and Tadashi Mochizuki, who took us camping in Chiba.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1294,1295]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1294\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-1/\" class=\"wp-image-1294\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1295\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-2/\" class=\"wp-image-1295\"/><figcaption>Ino Zhèng Zāi splits wood at our campsite in Chiba, alongside Satoshi Yamane and Tadashi Mochizuki. </figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1296,1297,1298]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1296\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-3/\" class=\"wp-image-1296\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1297\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-4/\" class=\"wp-image-1297\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1298\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-5/\" class=\"wp-image-1298\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1299,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-6.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1299\"/><figcaption>Satoshi grabs a few winks after the campsite\'s been set up.</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1300],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-1 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-7.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1300\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-7/\" class=\"wp-image-1300\"/><figcaption>Inside the pie iron: Gruyère, Japanese milk bread, sliced okra, and ham, heating up for dinner. </figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">The Furniture Maker</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In Gifu Prefecture, we met Masaru Kawai, a woodworker who learned his craft by apprenticing under a furniture maker in Kyoto. We visited him at his workshop.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1301,1302]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-8.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1301\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-8/\" class=\"wp-image-1301\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-9.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1302\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-9/\" class=\"wp-image-1302\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Trees contain the history and memories of the land...no two trees are the same. Through different woods, you’re able to see different worlds.</p><cite>Masaru Kawai</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1303,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-10.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1303\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Masaru runs his business, SOMA, out of the workshop he shares with his uncle. He carefully chooses which wood to use, taking into consideration its age, variety, color, and even its life as a tree. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1304],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-1 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-11.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1304\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-11/\" class=\"wp-image-1304\"/><figcaption>\"Being able to read grains will change how you see trees, and changing how you see trees can make you see nature differently.” — Masaru Kawai</figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">The Soba Shop</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Honke Owariya is a 16th-generation Kyoto soba restaurant. Currently operated by Ariko Inaoka —&nbsp;who lives nearby with her husband, Sean Lotman — it got its start as a confectionery shop in 1465. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1305,1306]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-12.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1305\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-12/\" class=\"wp-image-1305\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-13.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1306\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-13/\" class=\"wp-image-1306\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Between making Japanese sweets and soba, Owariya has been operating for over half a millennium.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1307,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-14.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1307\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1308,1309]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-15.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1308\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-15/\" class=\"wp-image-1308\"/><figcaption>Ariko’s husband, Sean Lotman, showed us around their neighborhood. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-16.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1309\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-16/\" class=\"wp-image-1309\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>It is because we have sustained tradition while changing with the times and taking on new challenges that we have a 550-year history. This is something I learned directly from my father and grandfather. I take seriously the responsibility of running the family business, never forgetting our history, and deepening our connection to Kyoto.</p><cite>Ariko Inaoka</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1310],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-1 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-17.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1310\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/japan-craft-17/\" class=\"wp-image-1310\"/><figcaption>Rui Shimamoto joined the team in Japan as our videographer, documenting our adventures.</figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During our travels in Japan we observed an incredible dedication to and respect for craft, process, form, and precision — the same qualities we abide by at Best Made.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That commitment to craft is what we pursue in our own work. It’s a philosophy we profoundly respect. Indeed, it’s why we exist. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1311,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-18.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1311\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer -->\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Commitment to Craft','','publish','open','open','','japan-commitment-to-craft','','','2019-11-14 21:08:06','2019-11-14 21:08:06','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=392',0,'post','',0),(1541,8,'2019-12-03 22:09:03','2019-12-03 22:09:03','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mountaineers Niki Kemser, Hannes Brunner, and Robert Nagel were our guides as we descended Zugspitze, the highest peak in Germany. <br><br>We went there in pursuit of celebrating quality, utility, and wonder — traits we strive to bring to life through our products and the stories we tell. <br><br>In Bavaria, we found those qualities in spades: the best, boldest, and most wonderful people and places, from skilled workmen and farmers to soaring mountain peaks. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1582,1500]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain2a.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1582\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_mountain2a/\" class=\"wp-image-1582\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1500\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_mountain3/\" class=\"wp-image-1500\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We ascended the mountain — which rises nearly 9,718 feet above sea level — by cable car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1502,1503,1504]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1502\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_mountain5/\" class=\"wp-image-1502\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1503\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_mountain6/\" class=\"wp-image-1503\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain7.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1504\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_mountain7/\" class=\"wp-image-1504\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Home to three glaciers, the towering peak commands views into four neighboring countries.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1501,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":900,\"height\":600} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1501\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before the descent, Niki paused to eat a bar of Ritter Sport. The popular chocolate brand is a classic hiking snack throughout Europe.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1505,1506,1583]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain8.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1505\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_mountain8/\" class=\"wp-image-1505\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain9.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1506\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_mountain9/\" class=\"wp-image-1506\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain10a.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1583\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_mountain10a/\" class=\"wp-image-1583\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Over the next three hours, Niki, Robert, and Hannes led us down the rocky mountainside. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1558,1559]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain11a.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1558\" data-link=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?attachment_id=1558\" class=\"wp-image-1558\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain12a.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1559\" data-link=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?attachment_id=1559\" class=\"wp-image-1559\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our trek ended at Knorrhütte. Owned by the German Alpine Club, the small mountain hut has been an important base for hikers climbing Zugspitze since its construction in 1855. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1510,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":900,\"height\":600} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Mountain13.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1510\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Bavaria: The Mountain','','publish','open','open','','bavaria-the-mountaineers','','','2019-12-04 23:05:51','2019-12-04 23:05:51','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1541',0,'post','',0),(1542,8,'2019-12-03 18:06:31','2019-12-03 18:06:31','','Bavaria Mountain','','publish','closed','closed','','new-slideshow-22','','','2019-12-03 18:12:4