019-11-01 00:28:15','','Slider 297 - image','','publish','closed','closed','','slider-297-image-4','','','2019-11-07 15:15:03','2019-11-07 15:15:03','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=ml-slide&#038;p=595',2,'ml-slide','',0),(1364,8,'2019-11-14 22:08:16','2019-11-14 22:08:16','','Camping Knives Thumbnail','','inherit','open','closed','','camping-knives-thumbnail','','','2019-11-14 22:08:16','2019-11-14 22:08:16','',346,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Camping-Knives-Thumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1535,8,'2019-12-03 22:08:59','2019-12-03 22:08:59','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On our latest adventure in Bavaria, Germany, we spent a day working with Bernhard Hage, who calls himself a \"woodshifter.\"<br><br>We went there in pursuit of celebrating quality, utility, and wonder — traits we strive to bring to life through our products and the stories we tell. <br><br>In Bavaria, we found those qualities in spades: the best, boldest, and most wonderful people and places, from skilled workmen and farmers to soaring mountain peaks. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1549,1550]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter2.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1549\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_woodshifter2/\" class=\"wp-image-1549\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1550\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_woodshifter3/\" class=\"wp-image-1550\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Near his home in the Alps, Bernhard transports felled logs by horse. Typically, lumber is moved by machines that tear up the forest floor — Bernhard’s approach to \"woodshifting\" preserves both the land and a traditional practice. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1515,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":675,\"height\":450} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1515\" width=\"675\" height=\"450\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He works alone with his horse, Moritz, to move the massive logged trees from the woods to his workshop. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:metaslider/slider {\"slideshowId\":1536} -->\n<div class=\"alignnormal\">[metaslider id=1536 cssclass=\"\"]</div>\n<!-- /wp:metaslider/slider -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Each tree is seasoned before being cut into lumber, timber, or sawnwood, destined to end up as buildings, furniture, and more.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1520,1521],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter9.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1520\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_woodshifter9/\" class=\"wp-image-1520\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter10.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1521\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_woodshifter10/\" class=\"wp-image-1521\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moritz — tucked in for the night, below — is exceptionally well behaved, and incredibly fast. So fast, in fact, that Bernhard occasionally has to ride the cut logs down the mountain like skis in order to keep up. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1522,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":900,\"height\":600} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter11.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1522\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Bavaria: The Forest','','publish','open','open','','bavaria-the-woodshifter','','','2019-12-05 22:28:38','2019-12-05 22:28:38','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1535',0,'post','',0),(1669,8,'2019-12-17 18:00:07','2019-12-17 18:00:07','','JJ Kelley 10 Questions FeatureB','','inherit','open','closed','','jj-kelley-10-questions-featureb','','','2019-12-17 18:00:07','2019-12-17 18:00:07','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/JJ-Kelley-10-Questions-FeatureB.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1670,8,'2019-12-17 18:00:12','2019-12-17 18:00:12','','JJ Kelley 10 Questions ThumbnailB','','inherit','open','closed','','jj-kelley-10-questions-thumbnailb','','','2019-12-17 18:00:28','2019-12-17 18:00:28','',1629,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/JJ-Kelley-10-Questions-ThumbnailB.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(517,8,'2019-11-01 16:38:04','2019-11-01 16:38:04','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As winter approaches, it’s a good idea to do some regular maintenance on your gear. Oil your boots, shake out your winter coats — and rewax any cotton or canvas that needs it.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>First, determine if your item needs rewaxing; check the areas that experience the most friction, like the elbows and knees.&nbsp;If you decide anything is in need of a thorough rewax, just follow these steps:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1288,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":675,\"height\":450} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rewaxing-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1288\" width=\"675\" height=\"450\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>First, clean the area — try scrubbing with water first, and if it\'s needed, use a bit of mild soap to clean heavily soiled areas.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next, warm the area of the garment with a hairdryer. This will relax the fibers in the fabric and help the wax to penetrate. Use your fingers to rub the garment as you heat it; sometimes, this will be all you need to redistribute enough wax to eliminate crease marks. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now you can apply the wax. Wearing a pair of vinyl gloves to protect your fingers, apply a small amount as evenly as possible by hand —&nbsp;using your fingers allows the heat from your hand to help keep the wax soft. The garment should start to take on a smooth waxy sheen. Apply a little extra wax to any seams.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1289,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":675,\"height\":450} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rewaxing-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1289\" width=\"675\" height=\"450\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Heat the wax with a hairdryer and rub it in vigorously with your fingers to help melt the wax into the fabric. The sheen will dissipate, but not entirely&nbsp;disappear. Continue heating and rubbing until the wax has completely melted and the fabric takes on a uniform appearance.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1290,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":675,\"height\":450} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rewaxing-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1290\" width=\"675\" height=\"450\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let the garment rest overnight to allow the wax to fully penetrate the fibers. To test the garment, spray it with water and let it sit for 10 minutes. If the water beads up and stays beaded it probably doesn’t need rewaxing. If the beads disappear into the fabric, it\'s time to start over. Reapply wax to any areas as needed. Remember that waxed cotton is <em>water-resistant</em>, not entirely <em>waterproof</em>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1291,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":675,\"height\":450} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rwaxing-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1291\" width=\"675\" height=\"450\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For the first few wearings, some of the surface wax may rub off onto nearby objects and garments, so keep the item away from anything delicate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Over time, the heat from your body will help the wax further penetrate into the fabric. Depending on the thickness of the fabric, some garments will need to be broken in again, but this shouldn’t take too long.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Remember</strong>: Never dry clean or wash a waxed garment in a washing machine. This will remove the wax and the whole garment will need to be rewaxed. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer -->\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Rewaxing','','publish','open','open','','rewaxing','','','2019-11-14 22:22:06','2019-11-14 22:22:06','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=517',0,'post','',0),(1288,8,'2019-11-14 20:44:26','2019-11-14 20:44:26','','Rewaxing 1','','inherit','open','closed','','rewaxing-1','','','2019-11-14 20:44:26','2019-11-14 20:44:26','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rewaxing-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1289,8,'2019-11-14 20:44:28','2019-11-14 20:44:28','','Rewaxing 2','','inherit','open','closed','','rewaxing-2','','','2019-11-14 20:44:28','2019-11-14 20:44:28','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rewaxing-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(753,8,'2019-11-06 15:33:09','2019-11-06 15:33:09','','LiveMakeBandana','','inherit','open','closed','','livemakebandana','','','2019-11-06 15:33:09','2019-11-06 15:33:09','',752,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/LiveMakeBandana.jpg',0,'attachmen