e.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1274,7,'2019-11-14 19:30:41','2019-11-14 19:30:41','','anchor_thumnail','','inherit','open','closed','','anchor_thumnail','','','2019-11-14 19:30:41','2019-11-14 19:30:41','',935,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/anchor_thumnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1614,8,'2019-12-06 22:21:37','2019-12-06 22:21:37','','Gift Guide - Axe Calendara','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-axe-calendara','','','2019-12-06 22:21:37','2019-12-06 22:21:37','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-Axe-Calendara.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1624,8,'2019-12-06 22:29:17','2019-12-06 22:29:17','','Gift Guide - Camp Blanketb','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-camp-blanketb','','','2019-12-06 22:29:17','2019-12-06 22:29:17','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-Camp-Blanketb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1616,8,'2019-12-06 22:21:42','2019-12-06 22:21:42','','Gift Guide - Cashmere CoCa','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-cashmere-coca','','','2019-12-06 22:21:42','2019-12-06 22:21:42','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-Cashmere-CoCa.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1617,8,'2019-12-06 22:21:43','2019-12-06 22:21:43','','Gift Guide - Crossbow Largea','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-crossbow-largea','','','2019-12-06 22:21:43','2019-12-06 22:21:43','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-Crossbow-Largea.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1618,8,'2019-12-06 22:21:45','2019-12-06 22:21:45','','Gift Guide - Down Pullovera','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-down-pullovera','','','2019-12-06 22:21:45','2019-12-06 22:21:45','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-Down-Pullovera.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1625,8,'2019-12-06 22:29:17','2019-12-06 22:29:17','','Gift Guide - Footlockerb','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-footlockerb','','','2019-12-06 22:29:17','2019-12-06 22:29:17','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-Footlockerb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1626,8,'2019-12-06 22:29:18','2019-12-06 22:29:18','','Gift Guide - Franklin Mugb','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-franklin-mugb','','','2019-12-06 22:29:18','2019-12-06 22:29:18','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-Franklin-Mugb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1621,8,'2019-12-06 22:21:48','2019-12-06 22:21:48','','Gift Guide - Hatcheta','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-hatcheta','','','2019-12-06 22:21:48','2019-12-06 22:21:48','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-Hatcheta.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1627,8,'2019-12-06 22:29:18','2019-12-06 22:29:18','','Gift Guide - Quilted Blanketb','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-quilted-blanketb','','','2019-12-06 22:29:18','2019-12-06 22:29:18','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-Quilted-Blanketb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1628,8,'2019-12-06 22:29:19','2019-12-06 22:29:19','','Gift Guide - Slipperb','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-slipperb','','','2019-12-06 22:29:19','2019-12-06 22:29:19','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-Slipperb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(496,8,'2019-09-28 16:19:43','2019-09-28 16:19:43','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The field journal is both a record of scientific data and a home for the feelings of the researcher. Though these roles seem to be at odds with one another —&nbsp;the first charged with gathering objective information, the second prone to romanticization —&nbsp;both share a wonder for the beauty and intricacy of the natural world. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ernest Thompson Seton embodied that contradiction; he was an ardent admirer of the natural landscape, and also a trapper with expertise in wolf hunting. Published in 1898, <em>Wild Animals I have Known</em> is a collection of Seton\'s short fiction based on Seton\'s experience in the natural world. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1367,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":675,\"height\":450} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Wild-Animals.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1367\" width=\"675\" height=\"450\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One legendary encounter is especially noteworthy: in 1883 Seton was hired in New Mexico to trap and kill a renegade wolf named Lobo, who had evaded all other attempts on his life. What Seton thought would be a two-week job turned into months of failed attempts. All the while, Seton was sketching the wildlife of New Mexico, falling in love with its natural beauty. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using notes from his experience with Lobo he wrote the short story <em>Lobo, the King of the Currumpaw</em>, in which Seton positions himself as the villain and Lobo as the unfortunate protagonist.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[499,500]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo2_500.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"499\" data-link=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?attachment_id=499\" class=\"wp-image-499\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo3_500.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"500\" data-link=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?attachment_id=500\" class=\"wp-image-500\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Seton had a gift for observing the actions and habits of animals and bringing out the personalities he saw in them. It would be easy to label this as mere anthropomorphization, but Seton’s writing is nuanced, transcending the typical “storybook” utilization of animal characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><em>… animals have no language in the full sense as we understand it, they have a system of sounds, signs, touches, tastes, and smells that answers the purpose of language, and I merely translate this, when necessary, into English.</em></p><cite>Ernest Thompson Seton</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After his experience hunting Lobo, Seton began to question the role humans played in the natural environment. He went on to influence the conservation movement of the early 20th-century, and was an influential founder of both the Boy Scouts of America and the Woodcraft movement.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":501,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo4_500.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-501\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ernest Thompson Seton died in 1975 but left behind a great number of journals and sketches of his observations of America\'s wildlife, as well as dozens of field manuals and short stories. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><em>Ever since Lobo, my sincerest wish has been to impress upon people that each of our native wild creatures is in itself a precious heritage that we have no right to destroy or put beyond the reach of our children.</em></p><cite>Ernest Thompson Seton</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We owe Seton a sizable debt of gratitude for helping to instill in the American psyche the value of our natural environment, and for his ability to touch our hearts in the way only a true storyteller can.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":498,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":412,\"height\":412} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo1_500.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-498\" width=\"412\" height=\"412\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->','Wild Animals I Have Known','','publish','open','open','','ernest-thompson-seton','','','2019-11-14 22:22:33','2019-11-14 22:22:33','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=496',0,'post','',0),(503,8,'2019-10-31 16:21:03','2019-10-31 16:21:03','','tumblr_m4e6upLXvN1qbqgxwo1_r3_1280','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_m4e6uplxvn1qbqgxwo1_r3_1280','','','2019-10-31 16:21:03','2019-10-31 16:21:03','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_m4e6upLXvN1qbqgxwo1_r3_1280.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(498,8,'2019-10-31 16:17:42','2019-10-31 16:17:42','','tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo1_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_m96oiemq2f1qbqgxwo1_500','','','2019-10-31 16:17:42','2019-10-31 16:17:42','',496,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo1_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(499,8,'2019-10-31 16:18:04','2019-10-31 16:18:04','','tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo2_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_m96oiemq2f1qbqgxwo2_500','','','2019-10-31 16:18:04','2019-10-31 16:18:04','',496,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo2_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(500,8,'2019-10-31 16:18:05','2019-10-31 16:18:05','','tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo3_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_m96oiemq2f1qbqgxwo3_500','','','2019-10-31 16:18:05','2019-10-31 16:18:05','',496,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo3_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(501,8,'2019-10-31 16:18:20','2019-10-31 16:18:20','','tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo4_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_m96oiemq2f1qbqgxwo4_500','','','2019-10-31 16:18:20','2019-10-31 16:18:20','',496,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_m96oiemQ2F1qbqgxwo4_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(504,8,'2019-09-12 16:26:00','2019-09-12 16:26:00','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a kid growing up in Minnesota, \"getting away from it all\" meant heading up north. Duluth. McGregor. Lutsen. The north shore. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We still love it up north. The fishing. The boating. And the cribbage, ah the cribbage. But for those days when the work starts to pile up, the emails need answering and I just can’t \"get away from it all,\" I have my Viewmaster. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":509,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":375,\"height\":332} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo2_500.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-509\" width=\"375\" height=\"332\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A few minutes clicking through the vistas of Gooseberry Falls, Split Rock Lighthouse, and the Silver Creek cliffs are almost as restorative as an actual visit. Almost. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:metaslider/slider {\"slideshowId\":732,\"containerClass\":\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio medium\"} -->\n<div class=\"alignnormal\">[metaslider id=732 cssclass=\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio medium\"]</div>\n<!-- /wp:metaslider/slider -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer -->\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','The Duluth Viewmaster','','publish','open','open','','duluth-viewmaster','','','2019-11-14 22:22:19','2019-11-14 22:22:19','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=504',0,'post','',0),(506,8,'2019-10-31 16:23:56','2019-10-31 16:23:56','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo3_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo3_500','','','2019-10-31 16:23:56','2019-10-31 16:23:56','',504,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo3_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(507,8,'2019-10-31 16:23:57','2019-10-31 16:23:57','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo6_r1_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo6_r1_500','','','2019-10-31 16:23:57','2019-10-31 16:23:57','',504,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo6_r1_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(508,8,'2019-10-31 16:23:58','2019-10-31 16:23:58','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo7_r1_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo7_r1_500','','','2019-10-31 16:23:58','2019-10-31 16:23:58','',504,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo7_r1_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(509,8,'2019-10-31 16:24:07','2019-10-31 16:24:07','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo2_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo2_500','','','2019-10-31 16:24:07','2019-10-31 16:24:07','',504,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo2_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(510,8,'2019-10-31 16:24:39','2019-10-31 16:24:39','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo8_r1_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo8_r1_500','','','2019-10-31 16:24:39','2019-10-31 16:24:39','',504,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo8_r1_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(511,8,'2019-10-31 16:24:40','2019-10-31 16:24:40','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo9_r1_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo9_r1_500','','','2019-10-31 16:24:40','2019-10-31 16:24:40','',504,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo9_r1_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(512,8,'2019-10-31 16:24:41','2019-10-31 16:24:41','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo10_r1_500','','inherit','open','closed','','tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo10_r1_500','','','2019-10-31 16:24:41','2019-10-31 16:24:41','',504,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/tumblr_lxp4i1k6aj1qbqgxwo10_r1_500.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1300,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:19','2019-11-14 20:58:19','','Japan Craft 7','Inside the pie iron: Gruyère, Japanese milk bread, sliced okra, and ham, heating up for dinner. ','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-7','','','2019-11-14 21:00:41','2019-11-14 21:00:41','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-7.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(482,7,'2019-10-31 15:46:43','2019-10-31 15:46:43','','Screen Shot 2019-10-31 at 11.46.32 AM','','inherit','open','closed','','screen-shot-2019-10-31-at-11-46-32-am','','','2019-10-31 15:46:43','2019-10-31 15:46:43','',478,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Screen-Shot-2019-10-31-at-11.46.32-AM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1629,8,'2019-12-21 17:04:22','2019-12-21 17:04:22','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>The Emmy-nominated filmmaker, producer, director, and explorer answers ten questions.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Optimism, pessimism, or stoicism?<br></strong>Optimism, always! We all have the capacity for greatness. However, I feel more and more people are opting to be negative. It seems the most divisive voices have the loudest platforms. These people are tearing us apart vs. building us up. As humans, we’re vulnerable alone, but our complex cooperation and coordination set us apart. If we don’t work together we will fail. I always look for the good in any situation or person, and because of that, I lead a much less stressful life. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>When do you get your best work done?<br></strong>In the stillness of morning. I travel internationally 60% of the time so my sleep schedule is often a mess. I find myself collapsing as the sun goes down and waking before it rises. The quiet of the morning invites focus, and the kaleidoscope of early morning sunlight gives me inspiration to be creative. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What do you rely on?<br></strong>A good story. Over my career, I’ve seen video production change formats from broadcast to streaming and from traditional networks to the digital content powerhouses of today, but a good story is timeless. Stories connect us, draw us in, and give us the courage to be better. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What’s an experience that changed you, and how?<br></strong>Kayaking from Alaska to Seattle. A best friend and I decided to build wooden boats and attempt what felt impossible: to paddle the length of North America’s Inside Passage. It was 97 days of rain, close bear encounters, and a whole lot of discomfort. That trip made me realize suffering isn’t as bad as we make it out to be. We all suffer, and suffering — no matter how profound — never lasts forever. I learned that if you’re comfortable when things aren’t perfect, then you can get through anything with a smile.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>When do you lose track of time?<br></strong>When I’m in the wild. I’ve spent more than a year of my life in a tent between various adventures. It’s in the out of doors where things slow down and the racing thoughts of constant productivity quiet. The wild is my place to recalibrate and as long as I keep an eye on when the sun will set, I’m happy to have time fly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What virtue or trait do you admire most in others?<br></strong>Accountability. I’ve worked in conflict zones and deep in the wild in places like Antarctica and the Congo. It’s in these extreme situations that I’ve come to realize that you need people around you who you can trust when plans fall apart. Too often in everyday life, we blow things off and don’t take into account the repercussions our actions — or lack thereof — have on others. From the banal to the most vital of tasks, I surround myself with people I can trust.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>When were you last outside of your comfort zone?</strong><br>Everyday! I make it a point to do something that freaks me out every single day. This is not to be mistaken for doing something that’s reckless. I’ve been to 111 countries and counting, and I’ve always come home. However, if I have the chance to eat at the local hot spot when others want to feed at the hotel, I venture out. Always venture out of your comfort zone; new and challenging experiences stimulate and strengthen your mind. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Why — or when — do you lie?</strong><br>I once got arrested in Tanzania. OK, but it wasn’t my fault. It was for a National Geographic film where we created fake elephant tusks to track down warlords profiting from the slaughter of wildlife. Our decoy tusks were so convincing that I was pulled off a plane and taken into custody as an international ivory smuggler. <br><br>Luckily, after just one night on the inside, the US Embassy came and bailed me out. Now I was free, but Tanzania wanted to know why I had fake tusks. I knew that if I told them it was for an investigation to find a warlord that they’d have more questions and perhaps hold me longer. I told them they were props for a film, which was kind of true, but that little lie got me on the next plane into the Congo. <a href=\"http://www.natgeotv.com/int/warlords-of-ivory/videos/trailer-warlords-of-ivory\">Those fake tusks eventually lead to the position of the war criminal Joseph Kony of the Lord’s Resistance Army. </a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Who’s your hero — real or fictional? </strong><br>My mom. She raised two kids without a dad. She worked two jobs and gave everything so we could go further. I owe everything I have today to her. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What question didn’t we ask that you were hoping we would? </strong><br>About a new series that I’m hosting on the Travel Channel! It’s called <a href=\"https://www.travelchannel.com/shows/lost-in-the-wild\"><em>Lost In The Wild</em></a>. In each episode, myself and journalist Kinga Philipps journey into the wilderness to track down answers to puzzling missing person cases. <br><br>As someone who’s taken chances while traveling the world, I’ve&nbsp;come to realize that I’m lucky to have always made it home. This isn’t the case for everyone who’s traveled, and I’ve made it my mission to tell their stories and to look for any new evidence that will bring closure to their case. From the Galapagos to the Himalayas, I had the chance to see some of the most extraordinary stretches of wilderness this planet has to offer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><a href=\"http://www.jjkelley.com/\"><strong>J.J. Kelley</strong></a><strong>&nbsp;is an Emmy-nominated filmmaker, producer, director, and explorer</strong> focused conservation issues and wildlife crime. An avid adventurer and fellow at the Explorers Club, Kelley brings a unique mix of humor and grit to his subjects — his new show, <em><a href=\"https://www.travelchannel.com/shows/lost-in-the-wild\">Lost in the Wild</a></em>, premieres December 29th.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer -->\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','10 Questions with J.J. Kelley','','publish','open','open','','10-questions-with-j-j-kelley','','','2019-12-21 17:04:24','2019-12-21 17:04:24','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1629',0,'post','',0),(493,8,'2019-11-05 15:59:43','2019-11-05 15:59:43','<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">Our adventures are a chance to put our gear to the test — in turn, they can have a breakthrough impact on the way we work. That’s what happened in Norway with our friend Martin Hartley, who showed us how critical it is that we all take responsibility for protecting the planet. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1322,1323]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/The-Good-Fight-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1322\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/the-good-fight-1/\" class=\"wp-image-1322\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/The-Good-Fight-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1323\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/the-good-fight-2/\" class=\"wp-image-1323\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">In remote Svalbard, where summertime temperatures hover in the 30s, the ice is melting. An expeditionist and photographer, Martin works to help scientists better understand our world, tracking the impact of the climate crisis.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1324]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-1 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/The-Good-Fight-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1324\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/the-good-fight-3/\" class=\"wp-image-1324\"/><figcaption>In order to safely cross the crevasse-riddled glacier and verify the condition of the ice, Martin and Matt roped themselves together. </figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">In Longyearbyen, Svalbard, he and videographer Matt Pycroft brought us along on a practice expedition: the conditions in arctic Svalbard make it the perfect location to prep for treks to the North Pole.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1325} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/The-Good-Fight-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1325\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1326} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/The-Good-Fight-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1326\"/><figcaption>Martin Hartley has spent over 400 days on the punishing Arctic Ocean.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Martin and Matt set out from the Polar Explorer warehouse in Longyearbyen, Svalbard. Before an actual trip begins they make practice runs, training themselves to acclimate to the elements and ensuring their gear is up to snuff. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:metaslider/slider {\"slideshowId\":1344} -->\n<div class=\"alignnormal\">[metaslider id=1344 cssclass=\"\"]</div>\n<!-- /wp:metaslider/slider -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Martin works to help track the impact of the climate crisis on the glaciers and polar ice caps, documenting their increasingly rapid disappearance. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1330,1331]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/The-Good-Fight-9.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1330\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/the-good-fight-9/\" class=\"wp-image-1330\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/The-Good-Fight-10.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1331\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/the-good-fight-10/\" class=\"wp-image-1331\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">To transport their gear, Martin and Matt strap themselves to a pulk —&nbsp;a type of Nordic sled — before trudging across the icy landscape. Svalbard is a place of extremes, of permafrost and endless light; it requires ironclad dedication to traverse. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:metaslider/slider {\"slideshowId\":1348} -->\n<div class=\"alignnormal\">[metaslider id=1348 cssclass=\"\"]</div>\n<!-- /wp:metaslider/slider -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1335,1336]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/The-Good-Fight-14.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1335\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/the-good-fight-14/\" class=\"wp-image-1335\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/The-Good-Fight-15.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1336\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/the-good-fight-15/\" class=\"wp-image-1336\"/><figcaption>Rocks help weigh down the tent in the face of bitter Arctic winds. </figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:metaslider/slider {\"slideshowId\":1353} -->\n<div class=\"alignnormal\">[metaslider id=1353 cssclass=\"\"]</div>\n<!-- /wp:metaslider/slider -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Under the light of the midnight sun, Martin and Matt finish setting up camp. The tent vestibule serves as a space to trap moisture, away from the sleeping area; inside, Martin brings water to boil for tea.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-0 is-cropped\"></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1342} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/The-Good-Fight-21.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1342\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We have always considered optimism a necessary tool to survival, and so we forge ahead with optimism first and foremost — but we can, and will, do more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><em>What do we lose as a species, if we choose to leave this moment alone? What do we risk, if we do nothing now? This is the only moment we have to prevent extinction on this planet, our only campsite, that we call home.&nbsp;</em></p><p><em>This time on your and my earth is impossibly small, smaller than any of us can realize.&nbsp;</em></p><p><em>These silent, nameless, and reclusive examples of Mother Nature’s architecture may be lost, perhaps forever. </em></p><p><em>We have a choice — the price we pay for that loss remains unknown. It is our moral duty to the universe to keep them present in any way we can.</em></p><cite>Martin Hartley</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer -->\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','The Good Fight','','publish','open','open','','svalbard-good-fight','','','2019-11-14 22:25:58','2019-11-14 22:25:58','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=493',0,'post','',0),(1589,8,'2019-12-09 15:31:10','2019-12-09 15:31:10','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Find the perfect gift for everyone on your list (and maybe something for yourself). From clothing to quilts and hatchets to calendars, Best Made products are built to work, designed to delight, and constructed to our exacting standard of quality. Quality never fails to inspire wonder.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator {\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator is-style-default\"/>\n<!-- 