 too good not to share. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ybb-HhSrtxA\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio small\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube aligncenter wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio small\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ybb-HhSrtxA\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">Hokuju</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h6 style=\"text-align:center\">The Art of Pottery</h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Shimizu Genji, known professionally as Hokuju, is a Master of Traditional Crafts at the Tokoname atelier, where he transforms raw clay into some of Japan\'s finest Ceramics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1184,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":470,\"height\":364,\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><a href=\"https://www.theparisreview.org/blog/2017/11/02/the-un-changing-ever-changing-earth-room/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/On-Dirt-pottery.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1184\" width=\"470\" height=\"364\"/></a></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">The Earth Room</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h6 style=\"text-align:center\">Unchanging and Evolving</h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Created by artist Walter De Maria over 40 years ago, this surreal installation features 140 tons of dirt in an incongruous city setting. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1183,\"align\":\"center\",\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://ediblehudsonvalley.ediblecommunities.com/food-thought/black-magic-hudson-valleys-special-soil\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/On-Dirt-muddy-hands.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1183\"/></a></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">Black Magic</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h6 style=\"text-align:center\">New York\'s Miracle Muck</h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">The roughly 26,000 acres of soil in Orange County\'s \"Black Dirt Region\" is some of the most fertile in the country, illegal to sell and intensely coveted.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cuICVsaxJxc\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio small\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio small\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cuICVsaxJxc\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">Dirt Road Blues</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h6 style=\"text-align:center\">Music Lesson</h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Born on Mississippi soil and considered the father of the Delta Blues, Charley Patton influenced generations of musicians. Here we celebrate his \"Down The Dirt Road Blues,\" released in 1929.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/vimeo {\"url\":\"https://vimeo.com/69225705?utm_campaign=2617611\\u0026utm_source=affiliate\\u0026utm_channel=affiliate\\u0026cjevent=f04c0d3efc0211e9811d00e40a24060e\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"vimeo\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio small\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio small\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://vimeo.com/69225705?utm_campaign=2617611&amp;utm_source=affiliate&amp;utm_channel=affiliate&amp;cjevent=f04c0d3efc0211e9811d00e40a24060e\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/vimeo -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">Sprouting</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<h6 style=\"text-align:center\">A Time-Lapse Film</h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">The impossible magic of germination, captured in a stunning two minute and twenty-five second time-lapse by Daniel Csobot.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><br>In the spring, at the end of the day, you should smell like dirt.</p><cite>Margaret Atwood</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->','On Dirt','','publish','open','open','','on-dirt','','','2019-11-14 23:13:23','2019-11-14 23:13:23','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=528',0,'post','',0),(1600,8,'2019-12-06 19:57:09','2019-12-06 19:57:09','','Gift Guide 2019 Feature','','inherit','open','closed','','gift-guide-2019-feature','','','2019-12-06 19:57:09','2019-12-06 19:57:09','',1589,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Gift-Guide-2019-Feature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1518,8,'2019-12-03 17:48:13','2019-12-03 17:48:13','','Bavaria_Woodshifter7','','inherit','open','closed','','bavaria_woodshifter7','','','2019-12-03 17:48:13','2019-12-03 17:48:13','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter7.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(478,7,'2019-10-31 15:50:52','2019-10-31 15:50:52','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>There are strange things done in the midnight sun / By the men who moil for gold; / The Arctic trails have their secret tales / That would make your blood run cold; / The Northern Lights have seen queer sights, / But the queerest they ever did see / Was that night on the marge of Lake Lebarge / I cremated Sam McGee.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And so begins <em>The Cremation of Sam McGee</em>, the most beloved, classic, chilling, haunting, colorful, and romantic children\'s poem that was ever written. Since childhood, this book has been — and remains —&nbsp;powerful fuel for the imagination. It\'s stories like this that keep us going. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Robert Service was one of the true great wilderness visionaries, and Johnny Cash\'s reading of his classic poem is a firm Best Made favorite.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yJNZwuamwj0\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio medium\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube aligncenter wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio medium\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yJNZwuamwj0\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Our Favorite Campfire Story','','publish','open','open','','cremation-sam-mcgee','','','2019-11-14 22:44:55','2019-11-14 22:44:55','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=478',0,'post','',0),(1519,8,'2019-12-03 17:48:16','2019-12-03 17:48:16','','Bavaria_Woodshifter8','','inherit','open','closed','','bavaria_woodshifter8','','','2019-12-03 17:48:16','2019-12-03 17:48:16','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter8.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1520,8,'2019-12-03 17:48:18','2019-12-03 17:48:18','','Bavaria_Woodshifter9','','inherit','open','closed','','bavaria_woodshifter9','','','2019-12-03 17:48:18','2019-12-03 17:48:18','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter9.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1521,8,'2019-12-03 17:48:19','2019-12-03 17:48:19','','Bavaria_Woodshifter10','','inherit','open','closed','','bavaria_woodshifter10','','','2019-12-03 17:48:19','2019-12-03 17:48:19','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter10.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1522,8,'2019-12-03 17:48:22','2019-12-03 17:48:22','','Bavaria_Woodshifter11','','inherit','open','closed','','bavaria_woodshifter11','','','2019-12-03 17:48:22','2019-12-03 17:48:22','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Woodshifter11.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1523,8,'2019-12-03 17:48:25','2019-12-03 17:48:25','','Bavaria_WoodshifterFeature','','inherit','open','closed','','bavaria_woodshifterfeature','','','2019-12-03 17:48:25','2019-12-03 17:48:25','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_WoodshifterFeature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1524,8,'2019-12-03 17:48:27','2019-12-03 17:48:27','','Bavaria_WoodshifterThumbnail','','inherit','open','closed','','bavaria_woodshifterthumbnail','','','2019-12-03 18:04:12','2019-12-03 18:04:12','',1535,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_WoodshifterThumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1525,8,'2019-12-03 22:09:06','2019-12-03 22:09:06','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Brothers Georg and Karl Schweisfurth run a guesthouse and organic farm in Bavaria, Germany. We went there in pursuit of celebrating quality, utility, and wonder — traits we strive to bring to life through our products and the stories we tell. <br><br>In Bavaria, we found those qualities in spades: the best, boldest, and most wonderful people and places, from skilled workmen and farmers to soaring mountain peaks. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:metaslider/slider {\"slideshowId\":1526} -->\n<div class=\"alignnormal\">[metaslider id=1526 cssclass=\"\"]</div>\n<!-- /wp:metaslider/slider -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Their father — the original Karl — founded Hermannsdorfer in 1986.  One of Europe\'s first organic farms, it was an early leader in the sustainability movement. <br><br>Ten years later, he turned the operation over to his son (the younger Karl), who in turn has handed most of the day-to-day work over to his daughter, Sophie. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1486,1487],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Farm5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1486\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_farm5/\" class=\"wp-image-1486\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Farm6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1487\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_farm6/\" class=\"wp-image-1487\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just down the road is Gut Sonnenhausen, where Karl\'s brother, Georg, runs a guesthouse for travelers. The two properties operate symbiotically — most of the ingredients for meals at Sonnenhausen are sourced from the farm at Herrmannsdorfer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:metaslider/slider {\"slideshowId\":1531} -->\n<div class=\"alignnormal\">[metaslider id=1531 cssclass=\"\"]</div>\n<!-- /wp:metaslider/slider -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The grounds at Sonnenhausen are also home to a few barnyard favorites. From sheep to chickens to horses, guests are able to interact with the animals.<br> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1491,1492,1493],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Farm10.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1491\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_farm10/\" class=\"wp-image-1491\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Farm11.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1492\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_farm11/\" class=\"wp-image-1492\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Farm12.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1493\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_farm12/\" class=\"wp-image-1493\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Andreas Merchant (above) moved his family to Hermannsdorfer to work for the two brothers in pursuit of his passion for quality ingredients and good food.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1494,1495],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Farm13.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1494\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_farm13/\" class=\"wp-image-1494\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Farm14.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1495\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/bavaria_farm14/\" class=\"wp-image-1495\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The austere and elegant buildings at Sonnenhausen were originally part of a 19th-century Bavarian farmhouse, which Georg and his family carefully restored.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1496,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Bavaria_Farm15.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1496\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tucked into this idyllic corner of Bavaria, the Schweisfurth family has spent the last 30+ years realizing their vision: living and working in harmony with nature. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Bavaria: The Farm','','publish','open','open','','bavaria-the-farm','','','2019-12-03 23:01:16','2019-12-03 23:01:16','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1525',0,'post','',0),(1526,8,'2019-12-03 17:53:53','2019-12-03 17:53:53','','Bavaria Farm 1','','publish','closed','closed','','new-slideshow-19','','','2019-12-03 18:13:24','2019-12-03 18:13:24','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=ml-slider&#038;p=1526',0,'ml-slider','',0),(1527,8,'2019-12-03 17:54:37','2019-12-03 17:54:37','','Slider 1526 - image','','publish','closed','closed','','slider-1526-image','','','2019-12-03 18:13:24','2019-12-03 18:13:24','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=ml-slide&#038;p=1527',0,'ml-slide','',0),(1528,8,'2019-12-03 17:54:45','2019-12-03 17:54:45','','Slider 1526 - image','','publish','closed','closed','','slider-1526-image-2','','','2019-12-03 18:13:24','2019-12-03 18:13:24','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=ml-slide&#038;p=1528',1,'ml-slide','',0),(1529,8,'2019-12-03 17:54:53','2019-12-03 17:54:53','','Slider 1526 - image','','publish','closed','closed','','slider-1526-image-3','','','2019-12-03 18:13:24','2019-12-03 18:13:24','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=ml-slide&#038;p=1529',2,'ml-slide','',0),(1530,8,'2019-12-03 17:55:00','2019-12-03 17:55:00','','Slider 1526 - image','','publish','closed','closed','','slider-1526-image-4','','','2019-12-03 18:13:24','2019-12-03 18:13:24','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=ml-slide&#038;p=1530',3,'ml-slide','',0),(1531,8,'2019-12-03 17:58:00','2019-12-03 17:58:00','','Bavaria Farm 2','','publish','closed','closed','','new-slideshow-20','','','2019-12-03 18:09:09','2019-12-03 18:09:09','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=ml-slider&#038;p=1531',0,'ml-slider','',0),(1532,8,'2019-12-03 17:58:13','2019-12-03 17:58:13','','Slider 1531 - image