l.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-6.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(787,8,'2019-11-06 17:02:12','2019-11-06 17:02:12','','Pad','','inherit','open','closed','','pad','','','2019-11-06 17:02:12','2019-11-06 17:02:12','',762,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Pad.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1301,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:22','2019-11-14 20:58:22','','Japan Craft 8','','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-8','','','2019-11-14 20:58:22','2019-11-14 20:58:22','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-8.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(789,8,'2019-11-06 17:05:49','2019-11-06 17:05:49','','Nalgene','','inherit','open','closed','','nalgene','','','2019-11-06 17:05:49','2019-11-06 17:05:49','',762,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Nalgene.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1302,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:25','2019-11-14 20:58:25','','Japan Craft 9','','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-9','','','2019-11-14 20:58:25','2019-11-14 20:58:25','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-9.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1417,8,'2019-11-21 20:07:59','2019-11-21 20:07:59','','American-Woolen-2','','inherit','open','closed','','american-woolen-2','','','2019-11-21 20:07:59','2019-11-21 20:07:59','',1414,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/American-Woolen-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1418,8,'2019-11-21 20:08:10','2019-11-21 20:08:10','','American-Woolen-1','','inherit','open','closed','','american-woolen-1','','','2019-11-21 20:08:10','2019-11-21 20:08:10','',1414,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/American-Woolen-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(727,8,'2019-11-05 21:01:30','2019-11-05 21:01:30','','ThumbnailSeton','','inherit','open','closed','','thumbnailseton','','','2019-11-05 21:01:30','2019-11-05 21:01:30','',496,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/ThumbnailSeton.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1296,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:10','2019-11-14 20:58:10','','Japan Craft 3','','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-3','','','2019-11-14 20:58:10','2019-11-14 20:58:10','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1297,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:12','2019-11-14 20:58:12','','Japan Craft 4','','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-4','','','2019-11-14 20:58:12','2019-11-14 20:58:12','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1719,8,'2020-01-15 15:58:12','2020-01-15 15:58:12','','Down Repel Spray','','publish','closed','closed','','down-repel-spray','','','2020-01-15 15:58:12','2020-01-15 15:58:12','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=1719',0,'product','',0),(881,8,'2019-08-31 16:29:44','2019-08-31 16:29:44','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are always chasing the light. On every Best Made shoot we’re up hours before dawn or patiently waiting for late afternoon, when the colors in the sky start to shift and blend, transforming the familiar landscape into something new. In Svalbard, the northernmost town on earth, light stands still.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To shoot a November catalog in August, we needed to find a location where it was cold enough to wear-test our products in inclement conditions. Martin Hartley and I have had a long-standing email friendship, and hoped that one day we could find an opportunity to work together; this year, it finally happened.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For Martin, Svalbard was significant and personal. It has been the jumping-off point for many of his expeditions. For most people, given the isolation and severity of the landscape, it might feel like the end of the world; for Martin, I imagine it feels like the beginning. <br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1223,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Svalbard-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1223\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During the pre-production process, the weather was a primary concern. The rapid increase in polar temperatures, melting permafrost, and increased rainfall meant that the snow that would have typically been present year-round was likely to be non-existent. Martin told me to wish for bad weather — bad weather would likely mean snow. Either way, we needed to find access to the more remote and inaccessible snowlines, which is what led us to the S/V Linden, the largest 3-mast wooden schooner still in operation in Europe.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Svalbard is a Norwegian archipelago, located 3 hours by plane from Oslo, and just 650 miles from the North Pole. Our first four days were spent aboard the S/V Linden. Before embarking, we sat down with Captain Rasmus to chart our course — each of our adventures start with a lot of discovery and end with a little bit of luck.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1224,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Svalbard-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1224\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Captain Rasmus and his crew charted a course, which included three glacial landings that would hopefully have snow, but would take 4-5 hours of sailing between each spot. Each landing required one of the crew members, accompanied by the ship’s husky, to do a preliminary sweep for polar bears.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1225,1226,1227]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Svalbard-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1225\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/svalbard-3/\" class=\"wp-image-1225\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Svalbard-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1226\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/svalbard-4/\" class=\"wp-image-1226\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Svalbard-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1227\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/svalbard-5/\" class=\"wp-image-1227\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is an innate quietness aboard the S/V Linden. You feel everywhere and nowhere at the same time. There is a specialness to Svalbard, a natural force that works hard to remind you of where you are. When glaciers break off — known as calving — it sounds like they are talking to you.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1228,1229,1230]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Svalbard-6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1228\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/svalbard-6/\" class=\"wp-image-1228\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Svalbard-7.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1229\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/svalbard-7/\" class=\"wp-image-1229\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Svalbard-8.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1230\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/svalbard-8/\" class=\"wp-image-1230\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our first landing was at 10:30 PM. The sky was still bright blue, masquerading as midday. As the tradition stands, the crew dropped the anchor and ended their day with a plunge into the Arctic Ocean, and encouraged us to do the same. I’ve been on 12 adventures with Best Made, and my favorite moments are always outside of the initial plan. There is a different kind of adventure that lives within these moments, with real people — and the opportunity to glimpse into extraordinary lives.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1231,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Svalbard-9.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1231\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->','Dispatches from Svalbard','','publish','open','open','','dispatches-svalbard','','','2019-11-14 22:19:37','2019-11-14 22:19:37','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=881',0,'post','',0),(801,7,'2019-11-09 15:32:53','2019-11-09 15:32:53','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>The chef,  adventurer,  poet, and larger than life iconoclast answers ten questions.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Optimism, pessimism, or stoicism?<br></strong>Always optimism. Stoicism has to do with a deep belief that can\'t be bent.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>When do you get your best work done?<br></strong>Always, always at dawn, that\'s why my younger daughter is called Alba.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What do you rely on?<br></strong>I rely mainly on patience first, and then on intuition.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What’s an experience that changed you, and how?<br></strong>Losing all my assets and starting again, because I realized that myself was still there, strong and willing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>When do you lose track of time?<br></strong>When I\'m on the island. No phone or Internet. I don\'t even know what day it is.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What’s your idea of hell?&nbsp;<br></strong>Cooking in-between two fires.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What virtue or trait do you admire most in others?<br></strong>The virtue of change. Saying: yes, I said yesterday was black but today I\'m certain it\'s white.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What are you reading, watching, or listening to lately?<br></strong>Reading <em>Our Immoral Soul</em> by Nilton Bonder, and everything related to disobedience. Listening to Beethoven\'s Symphony No. 7. Watching Visconti\'s films.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What’s something you love that most people hate?<br></strong>Irreverence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Who has had the most influence on you?<br></strong>My grandmother who was a couturier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer -->\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','10 Questions with Francis Mallmann','','publish','open','open','','x-questions-francis-mallmann','','','2019-12-09 19:04:57','2019-12-09 19:04:57','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=801',0,'post','',0),(1419,8,'2019-11-21 20:08:43','2019-11-21 20:08:43','','American-Woolen-3','','inherit','open','closed','','american-woolen-3','','','2019-11-21 20:08:43','2