8</blockquote></div>','','','publish','closed','closed','','fd91eb93f984152f81e850d6e4680e1d','','','2019-11-05 22:37:35','2019-11-05 22:37:35','',0,'https://editorial.bestmadeco.com/uncategorized/fd91eb93f984152f81e850d6e4680e1d/',0,'oembed_cache','',0),(749,8,'2019-06-30 22:52:34','2019-06-30 22:52:34','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A little savory, a little sweet, this delicious cornbread recipe from Momofuku Ssäm Bar&nbsp;Executive Chef Max Ng makes for a faultless dessert. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Cornbread</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Serves 8<br></h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Ingredients:</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>1 cup finely ground yellow cornmeal</li><li>1/4 cup all-purpose flour</li><li>2/3 cup granulated sugar</li><li>1 1/2 tsp baking soda</li><li>1/2 tbsp baking powder</li><li>1 tsp kosher salt</li><li>4 eggs</li><li>1 cup buttermilk</li><li>1 cup canned creamed corn</li><li>1 stick unsalted butter, melted, plus 1 tbsp cold</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Toppings:</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Several scoops of vanilla ice cream</li><li>1 cup Blueberry and Red Wine Compote (recipe below)</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":40} -->\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Directions:</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Whisk the cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, and salt together in a large bowl and set aside.&nbsp;</li><li>In a second bowl, whisk together eggs, buttermilk, and creamed corn.</li><li>Mix the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and whisk until combined.</li><li>Slowly stream the melted butter into the batter, and whisk to combine.</li><li>Chill the batter overnight, or up to three days (this hydrates the cornmeal).&nbsp;</li><li>When you’re ready to bake, preheat the oven to 375ºF.&nbsp;</li><li>Remove the batter from the refrigerator and mix well to reincorporate all the ingredients.</li><li>Preheat a 10” cast iron skillet over medium heat, and melt 1 tbsp butter until just beginning to brown.</li><li>Pour the batter into the skillet and bake for approximately 15 minutes. The idea is to undercook the cornbread so that it is soft to the touch and wobbles in the center.&nbsp;</li><li>Remove from the oven and allow to cool for 10 minutes.</li><li>Top with ice cream and Blueberry and Red Wine Compote before serving.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Blueberry and Red Wine Compote</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Ingredients:</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>1 cup red wine</li><li>1/2 cup sugar</li><li>1-pint blueberries</li><li>1/2 lemon, juiced</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Directions:</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Add red wine and sugar to a medium skillet over medium-high heat.</li><li>Once the sugar is melted and the mixture is bubbling, reduce heat and simmer for about 5 minutes. The mixture should thicken and coat the back of a spoon.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Add the blueberries, and continue to cook for an additional 5 minutes.</li><li>Remove from heat and stir in the lemon juice.</li><li>Set aside and allow to cool.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":70} -->\n<div style=\"height:70px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5><strong>Max Ng, Executive Chef, Momofuku Ssäm Bar&nbsp;</strong></h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A Singapore native, Max Ng came to New York with the sole intention of working for Momofuku. Prior to the move, he worked within the Les Amis Group in Singapore. At Momofuku, he started off as a CIA extern at Ssäm Bar, then moved on to Ko as a commis, eventually moving up as a line cook. Since then, he has risen to Sous Chef then Chef de Cuisine at Ko. In 2017, Max was appointed Executive Chef of Momofuku Ssäm Bar.&nbsp; </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Skillet Cornbread','','publish','open','open','','skillet-cornbread','','','2019-11-14 22:21:26','2019-11-14 22:21:26','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=749',0,'post','',0),(1295,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:09','2019-11-14 20:58:09','','Japan Craft 2','Ino Zhèng Zāi splits wood at our campsite in Chiba, alongside Satoshi Yamane and Tadashi Mochizuki. ','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-2','','','2019-11-14 20:59:42','2019-11-14 20:59:42','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(641,8,'2019-11-05 19:12:56','2019-11-05 19:12:56','','The Hobo Knife','','publish','closed','closed','','the-hobo-knife','','','2019-11-05 19:12:56','2019-11-05 19:12:56','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?pos