4','2019-11-14 17:09:44','',762,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/10-cast-iron-skillet.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1402,8,'2019-11-14 23:01:56','2019-11-14 23:01:56','','Best-Axes-Husqvarna','','inherit','open','closed','','best-axes-husqvarna','','','2019-11-14 23:01:56','2019-11-14 23:01:56','',818,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Best-Axes-Husqvarna.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(841,8,'2019-11-07 15:17:42','2019-11-07 15:17:42','','WIldAnimalsFeature','','inherit','open','closed','','wildanimalsfeature','','','2019-11-07 15:17:42','2019-11-07 15:17:42','',496,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/WIldAnimalsFeature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1298,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:14','2019-11-14 20:58:14','','Japan Craft 5','','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-5','','','2019-11-14 20:58:14','2019-11-14 20:58:14','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-5.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(882,8,'2019-03-21 16:31:13','2019-03-21 16:31:13','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the most common questions I get is “Why do you paint the desert?”&nbsp;I feel like I am supposed to come up with a deep and meaningful explanation, but it comes down to a feeling.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The root of why I paint the subjects that I paint is the feeling I get when I’m in a remote corner of the American Southwest.&nbsp;There is quiet loneliness to the desert that is haunting and attractive to me.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1213,1214]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Logan-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1213\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/logan-1/\" class=\"wp-image-1213\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Logan-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1214\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/logan-2/\" class=\"wp-image-1214\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The stark landscapes make sense to me from a visual standpoint — my brain is able to organize the big shapes of the desert in a way that aligns with my personal aesthetics.&nbsp; The big sky, mesas or mountains, and the earth dotted with patterns of puffy of sagebrush: all of it is what attracted me to the desert.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1215,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Logan-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1215\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After years of exploring the desert and painting its landscapes, I felt like I wanted to begin representing the people who lived in these places I was documenting; slowly, a small figure on horseback snuck into a composition.&nbsp;Later, as I got to know more desert dwellers, the human element began to assert equal importance in my compositions.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1216,1217]} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Logan-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1216\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/logan-4/\" class=\"wp-image-1216\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Logan-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1217\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/logan-5/\" class=\"wp-image-1217\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I try to think of the people in my paintings as an extension of the land itself. This connection to place is something that’s easy to tap into, in the quiet of the desert.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>The harmony between people and land is much more apparent in wild parts of the world.</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Frankly, it feels unnatural for me to articulate why I paint the things that I paint, because I have a hard time even putting it into words for myself. I’ve found it’s easy to overthink things into the ground, so I try to rely on my instincts and paint whatever happens to come out of me, without judgment.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The need to produce art is like a pang of hunger that is always there, making me aware of its presence. I feed that hunger to make art, and for a while, I feel satisfied — and then I’m hungry again.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer -->\n<div style=\"height:100px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','A Connection to Place','','publish','open','open','','connection-place','','','2019-11-14 22:18:58','2019-11-14 22:18:58','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=882',0,'post','',0),(1445,8,'2019-11-28 05:22:38','2019-11-28 05:22:38','','MallmannPotatoesThumbnail','','inherit','open','closed','','mallmannpotatoesthumbnail','','','2019-11-28 05:22:38','2019-11-28 05:22:38','',1444,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannPotatoesThumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1446,8,'2019-11-28 05:23:05','2019-11-28 05:23:05','','MallmannPotatoesFeature','','inherit','open','closed','','mallmannpotatoesfeature','','','2019-11-28 05:23:05','2019-11-28 05:23:05','',1444,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannPotatoesFeature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1461,8,'2019-11-28 18:41:25','2019-11-28 18:41:25','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The National Thanksgiving Turkey Presentation dates back to 1947, and entails presenting the President of the United States with a live turkey. A handful — Kennedy, Nixon, and Carter (who flat out refused to take part in any of it) — would occasionally spare the birds presented to them. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It wasn\'t until Reagan began sending his turkeys off to petting zoos — to deflect from more difficult political questions — that the \"official\" notion of the pardon came into play, a tradition which George H.W. Bush cemented.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, what does it take to make it in front of the President? 50 to 80 birds, chosen from the farm of the sitting National Turkey Federation (NTF) chairperson, are whittled down to the 10 or 20 best preened and best behaved. Two finalists are chosen, named, and flown to Washington, where the NTF puts them up in a hotel to await their fate at the White House. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>He is besides, though a little vain and silly, a bird of courage, and would not hesitate to attack a grenadier of the British Guards who should presume to invade his farmyard with a red coat on.</p><cite>Benjamin Franklin</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Beg Your Pardon','','publish','open','open','','beg-your-pardon','','','2019-11-28 18:41:26','20