,(1310,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:41','2019-11-14 20:58:41','','Japan Craft 17','Rui Shimamoto joined the team in Japan as our videographer, documenting our adventures.','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-17','','','2019-11-14 21:06:41','2019-11-14 21:06:41','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-17.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1311,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:43','2019-11-14 20:58:43','','Japan Craft 18','','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-18','','','2019-11-14 20:58:43','2019-11-14 20:58:43','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-18.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1312,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:46','2019-11-14 20:58:46','','Japan Craft Feature','','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-feature','','','2019-11-14 20:58:46','2019-11-14 20:58:46','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-Feature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1313,8,'2019-11-14 20:58:48','2019-11-14 20:58:48','','Japan Craft Thumbnail','','inherit','open','closed','','japan-craft-thumbnail','','','2019-11-14 21:07:04','2019-11-14 21:07:04','',392,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Japan-Craft-Thumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1379,7,'2019-11-14 22:30:04','2019-11-14 22:30:04','','bmc_060519_mushroom_knife_0003_GW_MG','','inherit','open','closed','','bmc_060519_mushroom_knife_0003_gw_mg','','','2019-11-14 22:30:04','2019-11-14 22:30:04','',1377,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/bmc_060519_mushroom_knife_0003_GW_MG.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1744,8,'2020-01-22 19:34:39','2020-01-22 19:34:39','','Wool Care Thumbnail','','inherit','open','closed','','wool-care-thumbnail','','','2020-01-22 19:34:39','2020-01-22 19:34:39','',1743,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Wool-Care-Thumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1745,8,'2020-01-22 19:35:02','2020-01-22 19:35:02','','Wool Care Feature','','inherit','open','closed','','wool-care-feature','','','2020-01-22 19:35:02','2020-01-22 19:35:02','',1743,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Wool-Care-Feature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1746,8,'2020-01-22 19:41:42','2020-01-22 19:41:42','','Sweater Stone','','publish','closed','closed','','sweater-stone','','','2020-01-22 19:41:42','2020-01-22 19:41:42','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=1746',0,'product','',0),(1747,8,'2020-01-22 19:41:37','2020-01-22 19:41:37','','Sweater Stone','','inherit','open','closed','','sweater-stone','','','2020-01-22 19:41:37','2020-01-22 19:41:37','',1746,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Sweater-Stone.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1377,7,'2019-11-14 22:30:15','2019-11-14 22:30:15','','Multipurpose Mushroom Knife','','publish','closed','closed','','multipurpose-mushroom-knife','','','2019-11-14 22:30:15','2019-11-14 22:30:15','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=1377',0,'product','',0),(1376,8,'2019-11-14 22:28:54','2019-11-14 22:28:54','','SamMcgee Thumbnail','','inherit','open','closed','','sammcgee-thumbnail','','','2019-11-14 22:28:54','2019-11-14 22:28:54','',478,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SamMcgee-Thumbnail.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1444,8,'2019-11-26 20:04:55','2019-11-26 20:04:55','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A tip: when you boil your potatoes for smashing, it’s important to start them in cold water. They cook more gently that way, and are less likely to break up and become soggy. Add olive oil, vinegar, bay leaves, and pepper to the cooking water for subtle flavor. If you\'ll be cooking outdoors, parboil the potatoes ahead of time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Francis Mallmann\'s Smashed Potatoes</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Serves 4<br></h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Ingredients:</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>4 red or white all-purpose potatoes, about 5 oz each, well-scrubbed</li><li>2 tbsp red wine vinegar</li><li>6 tbsp extra virgin olive oil</li><li>1 bay leaf</li><li>¼ tsp black peppercorns</li><li>Coarse salt</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":40} -->\n<div style=\"height:40px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Directions:</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Put the potatoes in a large saucepan and add the red wine vinegar, 2 tablespoons of the olive oil, the bay leaf, peppercorns, and salt to taste. Cover with cold water and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium and cook at a low boil for 12 to 15 minutes, or until the potatoes are tender enough to be pierced through with a skewer. Drain in a colander; do not allow them to cool, or they will break instead of smash.<br></li><li>Put a potato on a clean dishcloth on a work surface, cover with another clean dishcloth, and using the palm of your hand, slowly and gently smash the potato. Transfer to a tray. Repeat with the remaining potatoes. Spoon the remaining ¼ cup olive oil over the potatoes.<br></li><li>Heat a <em>chapa</em> or large cast-iron griddle over medium-low heat until a drop of water sizzles on the surface. Put the potatoes on the hot surface, oiled side down, and cook for around 40 minutes until they are crisp: <em>don’t move them!</em></li><li>Carefully remove the potatoes as they are cooked and invert onto a serving platter, crisp side facing up. Serve immediately.&nbsp;</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Francis Mallmann</strong>, a longtime friend of Best Made and our Creative Advisor, is an Argentine chef and author. An adventurous spirit known for his open-fire cooking, Mallmann owns restaurants in Mendoza, Buenos Aires, Uruguay, Miami, Chile, and France.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Smashed Potatoes','','publish','open','open','','smashed-potatoes','','','2019-12-12 20:06:24','2019-12-12 20:06:24','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1444',0,'post','',0),(1399,8,'2019-11-14 22:58:55','2019-11-14 22:58:55','','Best-Axes-Estwing-Sportsman','','inherit','open','closed','','best-axes-estwing-sportsman','','','2019-11-14 22:58:55','2019-11-14 22:58:55','',818,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Best-Axes-Estwing-Sportsman.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1400,8,'2019-11-14 22:59:37','2019-11-14 22:59:37','','Best-Axes-Schrade','','inherit','open','closed','','best-axes-schrade','','','2019-11-14 22:59:37','2019-11-14 22:59:37','',818,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Best-Axes-Schrade.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1401,8,'2019-11-14 23:00:47','2019-11-14 23:00:47','','Best-Axes-Gransfors','','inherit','open','closed','','best-axes-gransfors','','','2019-11-14 23:00:47','2019-11-14 23:00:47','',818,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Best-Axes-Gransfors.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1183,8,'2019-11-14 17:52:30','2019-11-14 17:52:30','','On Dirt - muddy hands','','inherit','open','closed','','on-dirt-muddy-hands','','','2019-11-14 17:52:30','2019-11-14 17:52:30','',528,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/On-Dirt-muddy-hands.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1184,8,'2019-11-14 17:52:31','2019-11-14 17:52:31','','On Dirt - pottery','','inherit','open','closed','','on-dirt-pottery','','','2019-11-14 17:52:31','2019-11-14 17:52:31','',528,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/On-Dirt-pottery.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1185,8,'2019-11-14 17:52:32','2019-11-14 17:52:32','','On Dirt Feature','','inherit','open','closed','','on-dirt-feature','','','2019-11-14 17:52:32','2019-11-14 17:52:32','',528,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/On-Dirt-Feature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1742,8,'2020-01-22 17:54:46','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2020-01-22 17:54:46','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1742',0,'post','',0),(1642,8,'2020-01-02 18:05:52','2020-01-02 18:05:52','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Boundary Waters is special. Its awe-inspiring landscape was shaped by glaciers millennia ago. At nearly 1.1 million acres, it spreads across the Northeastern tip of Minnesota — a vast boreal forest of interconnected lakes, streams, wetlands, and aquifers that provide some of the best fishing and hunting in the world.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1652,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":900,\"height\":600} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1652\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I’m privileged to have the Boundary Waters Canoe Area (BWCA) practically be my backyard. I’ve lived in Minnesota my entire life. My dad first brought me to the BWCA when I was twelve, on a fishing trip — since then I’ve spent nearly 200 nights there.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1653,1651],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1653\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/ice-fishing-3/\" class=\"wp-image-1653\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1651\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/ice-fishing-1/\" class=\"wp-image-1651\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ice fishing for lake trout is something else. It provides a special kind of solace, and to even get started you have to trudge through the snow pulling a pulk sled loaded with survival gear. It’s intentional in a way few things are, and there’s not much better than cooking a freshly caught fish out on the ice. If you’re interested in trying it out for yourself, I’ve got a few tips before you get started.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1666,1654],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-13.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1666\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/ice-fishing-13/\" class=\"wp-image-1666\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1654\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/ice-fishing-4/\" class=\"wp-image-1654\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3,\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><strong>5 Tips for Cooking on Ice</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Find the Right Spot</em></strong><br>Look for a place that will shelter your fire from the wind: behind a rock, tucked into the woods at the lake’s edge, or somewhere where your gear can act as a windbreak.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Set Up</em></strong><br>When you’ve picked a spot, clear an area for the fire and pack down the snow to make a workspace. Gather a handful of green pine boughs, a wood platform, or a metal pan — something to insulate your fire from the ice.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1656,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":900,\"height\":600} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-6.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1656\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Get Fuel</em></strong><br>Start cutting or collecting branches from downed trees. Make sure to get different sizes, everything from small kindling to wrist-sized logs — you can use birch bark as a fire starter, but remember never to take it from a live tree.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1659,1657],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-9.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1659\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/ice-fishing-9/\" class=\"wp-image-1659\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-7.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1657\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/ice-fishing-7/\" class=\"wp-image-1657\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Prep Your Food</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Fillet your lake trout (my favorite recipe, below), chop your vegetables, get out your ribeyes — whatever you’re cooking, make sure everything’s in place before you get started, from seasonings to utensils.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1660,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":900,\"height\":600} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-10.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1660\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><em>Start Cooking</em></strong><br>Get your fire blazing and build some coals. Keep a low level of flame going at all times. Set your cast iron pan on two logs, to give yourself room to feed the fire as needed. An old tip: say “white rabbit” as you cook to keep the smoke for blowing into your face. And remember to always clean up your ashes and leave no trace when you’re done!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1661,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":900,\"height\":600} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-11.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1661\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I’m cooking like this, there’s nothing fancy involved — just the fish, the fire, and the elements. While my exact recipe has changed over the years, the goal is always to highlight the trout itself. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This particular recipe just happens to be the style that I am infatuated with at the moment. It’s quite simple, and I don’t doubt that I’ll get a laugh out of you from the ingredients list — yellow mustard, ground Cheez-its, and Hungry Jack pancake mix.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You’re smiling, right? Trust me. Make it. Cooked in a bunch of butter or bacon grease and this fish is the breakfast, lunch, and dinner of champions. Serve it alone or with whatever you like on the side.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1662,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":900,\"height\":600} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-12.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1662\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Pan-Fried Lake Trout</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Ingredients:</em> <br>Two skinless lake trout fillets, about 8 oz each&nbsp;<br>1⁄4 cup yellow mustard<br>1 cup Cheez-its, finely crushed <br>1⁄2 cup of pancake mix<br>4 oz of bacon fat or butter</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Directions:</em>						</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Filet the trout. Make sure there are no bones, rinse the fish, and set it aside.&nbsp;</li><li>Add the mustard to a small bowl or plastic bag. Add the trout fillets and make sure they’re entirely coated with mustard. Do not do this too far ahead of time, as the vinegar in the mustard will begin to cold cook the fish, changing the texture when you pan fry it.</li><li>In a separate plastic bag, combine the Cheez-its and pancake mix. Shake to mix thoroughly. Place the mustard fillets in the breading and shake vigorously. Leave in the bag.</li><li>Begin heating a cast iron pan over the fire. To test the heat, throw a little bacon fat or butter in the pan. If it begins to sizzle, add the rest of the fat and place the fish in the pan.&nbsp;</li><li>Sear the fish until the edges begin to brown. Flip and repeat. Each side will take about 3-4 minutes. Check to make sure the fillets are fully cooked before serving.&nbsp;</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1658,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":330,\"height\":495} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ice-Fishing-8.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1658\" width=\"330\" height=\"495\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Boundary Waters is a deeply meaningful place to me. I’m fortunate to work full time as the Executive Director of <a href=\"https://sportsmenbwca.org/\">Sportsmen for the Boundary Waters</a>, which ensures that this vital resource remains protected, and continues to exist as it does today for generations to come. <br><br>For more information on the Boundary Waters and how you can help preserve it, visit <a href=\"https://sportsmenbwca.org/\">sportsmenbwca.org</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Lukas Leaf </strong>is a chef and avid outdoorsman who serves as the Executive Director of Sportsmen for the Boundary Waters. He\'s spent his life fishing, foraging, hunting, camping, and cooking in the Minnesota wilderness, and is passionate about protecting our planet\'s natural resources. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":50} -->\n<div style=\"height:50px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Ice Fishing in the Boundary Waters','','publish','open','open','','ice-fishing-in-the-boundary-waters','','','2020-01-02 18:05:54','2020-01-02 18:05:54','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1642',0,'post','',0),(1405,8,'2019-11-14 23:20:18','2019-11-14 23:20:18','','Blog Banner update','','inherit','open','closed','','blog-banner-update','','','2019-11-14 23:20:18','2019-11-14 23:20:18','',9,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Blog-Banner-update.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1423,8,'2019-11-25 17:22:22','2019-11-25 17:22:22','','The Wool Flannel Ball Cap','','publish','closed','closed','','the-wool-flannel-ball-cap','','','2019-11-25 17:22:22','2019-11-25 17:22:22','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?post_type=product&#038;p=1423',0,'product','',0),(1424,8,'2019-11-25 17:22:06','2019-11-25 17:22:06','','Wool Flannel Ball Cap','','inherit','open','closed','','wool-flannel-ball-cap','','','2019-11-25 17:22:06','2019-11-25 17:22:06','',1423,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Wool-Flannel-Ball-Cap.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1425,8,'2019-11-20 20:04:38','2019-11-20 20:04:38','<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":25} -->\n<div style=\"height:25px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our latest collection with legendary chef — and Best Made Creative Advisor — Francis Mallmann speaks to life\'s richest moments, both at home and on the road.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In celebration of its launch, we hosted a fall cookout at Brooklyn\'s McCarren park, where Mallmann himself manned the grills.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:metaslider/slider {\"slideshowId\":1447} -->\n<div class=\"alignnormal\">[metaslider id=1447 cssclass=\"\"]</div>\n<!-- /wp:metaslider/slider -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Francis was the first to arrive on Sunday morning, getting the fires going in the chilly darkness before sunrise. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As the team trickled in and began quietly and efficiently setting things up, there was a moment of perfect equilibrium — a space where work and passion were one and the same. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1426],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-1 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannMcCarren1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1426\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/mallmannmccarren1/\" class=\"wp-image-1426\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For Mallmann, it is the tension between those ideas that brings depth to our days, particularly where they meet within the context of entertaining. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hosting friends and family is both a labor and a joy; a contradiction at the heart of this new collection. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaId\":1433,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannMcCarren8.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1433\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"My credo — my belief — is that life’s richest moments occur at the intersection of home, travel, love, taste, and wilderness, even at the edge of uncertainty.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This collection is designed to enable those moments and a way of living, a recipe of passion, family, adventure, and work, mixed up on the road and tempered with fire, embers, and coals.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>—&nbsp;Francis Mallmann</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">The menu was classic Mallmann: an exultation of fire and smoke and simple, well-prepared ingredients — the ribeye alone was slow-roasted on the grill for four hours. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[1429,1430,1432],\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery aligncenter columns-3 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannMcCarren4.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1429\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/mallmannmccarren4/\" class=\"wp-image-1429\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannMcCarren5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1430\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/mallmannmccarren5/\" class=\"wp-image-1430\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannMcCarren7.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"1432\" data-link=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/mallmannmccarren7/\" class=\"wp-image-1432\"/></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Steak and chimichurri sandwiches; savory pumpkin soup; vegetable sandwiches; an almond cake cooked on the <em>plancha</em> and served with strawberry jam, and dulce de leche.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:metaslider/slider {\"slideshowId\":1455} -->\n<div class=\"alignnormal\">[metaslider id=1455 cssclass=\"\"]</div>\n<!-- /wp:metaslider/slider -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This cookout was our way of throwing open the doors and bringing people into Francis\' world. Nearly 2000 people came out on Sunday to have a bite, talk, and pass the time — we couldn\'t be more grateful to everyone who stopped by. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When we are able to find ways to make space for warmth, elegance, and inspiration wherever we find ourselves, anywhere can feel like home. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":20} -->\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1431,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":900,\"height\":600} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannMcCarren6.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1431\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":30} -->\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>I wanted to thank everyone for the incredible, loving job done. It was a miracle for me. Full of surprises. We went all the way to glory with the lunch. Thanks for being so inspiring.</p><cite>Francis Mallmann</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":60} -->\n<div style=\"height:60px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->','Mallmann at McCarren','','publish','open','open','','mallmann-at-mccarren','','','2019-12-03 20:15:55','2019-12-03 20:15:55','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/?p=1425',0,'post','',0),(1426,8,'2019-11-26 17:57:34','2019-11-26 17:57:34','','MallmannMcCarren1','','inherit','open','closed','','mallmannmccarren1','','','2019-11-26 17:57:34','2019-11-26 17:57:34','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannMcCarren1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1427,8,'2019-11-26 17:57:37','2019-11-26 17:57:37','','MallmannMcCarren2','','inherit','open','closed','','mallmannmccarren2','','','2019-11-26 17:57:37','2019-11-26 17:57:37','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannMcCarren2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1428,8,'2019-11-26 17:57:40','2019-11-26 17:57:40','','MallmannMcCarren3','','inherit','open','closed','','mallmannmccarren3','','','2019-11-26 17:57:40','2019-11-26 17:57:40','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannMcCarren3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1429,8,'2019-11-26 17:57:42','2019-11-26 17:57:42','','MallmannMcCarren4','','inherit','open','closed','','mallmannmccarren4','','','2019-11-26 17:57:42','2019-11-26 17:57:42','',0,'http://editorial.bestmadeco.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/MallmannMcCarren4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1430,8,'2019-11-26 17:57:43','2019-11-26 17:57:43','','MallmannMcCarren5','','inherit','open','close